__str__: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 1 :: Trust is Not a Feeling: Part 1
title: Trust is Not a Feeling: Part 1
description: Join Curt Landry as he brings a strategic word from the Lord. He explains that the Lord is weaning His people off their past schedules –God is seeking a Bride who operates inside of His perfect timing. While many of us have made decisions based on our emotions in the past, the Lord is rewiring our thought life, and requesting that we set aside our feelings in exchange for the truth of God’s Word.
season: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 1

__str__: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 1 :: Trust is Not a Feeling: Part 2
title: Trust is Not a Feeling: Part 2
description: Curt continues with a word that between Passover and Rosh Hashanah God is planning to cancel many debts. However, we are reminded that with great wealth comes greater responsibility –wealth is not a ticket to do whatever we wish. Although many of us have faced hard times, God has allowed these as a way to grow us into greater maturity, so that we might defeat the works of the enemy at a high level.
season: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 1

__str__: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 1 :: Realignment After Trials and Tests - Part 1
title: Realignment After Trials and Tests - Part 1
description: This message entitled, "Realignment After Trials and Tests" by Curt Landry, will teach you what you need to know in order to realign yourself while you are in the midst of the trials and tribulations of your life. "Your test will either become a teacher or a terrorist." You must be teachable, no matter how old or experienced you are. If you are teachable, you are empowered. In every situation, whether trial or test, this message will help you learn how to develop the outlook needed to weather your tribulation and give praise to Him through the storms. Listen as Curt teaches how you can find your trigger to impatience, learn how to dismantle it and have the victory over it. The principles that Curt Landry lays out in this message will empower you to become established and settled in Messiah. You can have peace and joy that flows like a river! Learn how you can make a daily decree to "Bless the Lord" and turn your trials and testing into joy and faith!
season: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 1

__str__: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 1 :: Power of Reconciliation with Guest Dr. Alveda King - Part 1
title: Power of Reconciliation with Guest Dr. Alveda King - Part 1
description: Curt Landry Ministries welcomes Dr. Alveda King as a very special and honored guest speaker. Dr. King shares from Hebrews chapter 12—revealing our greatest need to fully reconcile to God, our Father. Both she and Curt Landry take a portion of the service to discuss the significance of Abraham, the patriarch of the Hebrew nation. Curt Landry shares about the impatience of father Abraham and Sarah when they chose to have a child through their maid servant Hagar (Arab). Dr. King reminds us that we all bleed the same blood. It is time that the Body of Christ bridge the gap of race reconciliation through prayer and repentance.
season: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 1

__str__: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 1 :: Correction Leads to Victory and Destiny: Part 1
title: Correction Leads to Victory and Destiny: Part 1
description: Curt Landry explains that yesterday’s behaviour and choices will lead to yesterday’s results. He explains that we must first adjust our thinking. He then takes a brief moment to review the recent One New Man Conference, and the messages that were brought during that event. He goes on to share that the Lord is looking for someone He can “trust with His stuff.” He explains that we must first adjust our thinking. We have to understand that a double minded man is unsure in all of His ways. We cannot continue to process the third day through a second day understanding. He explains that we need to identify the cycles in our lives that continue to breed problems. We must examine the thoughts that consistently create trouble.
season: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 1

In this message, Curt Landry takes us through the stages of change with our covenant keeping Father. As we move toward God’s promotion in our lives, we see that pain and testing go together.

description:
In this message "Set your Year for Success 2018/5778 New Beginnings Reviewed" Curt Landry reveals that "your future is your focus". It's time to set your year for success in 2018! How many times have you set New Year's Resolutions only to find yourself going around the same mountain the following year?
 This is YOUR year! Through the help of the Holy Spirit, these steps will help you answer your unique call in this end time remnant. This year is a strategic time of realignment and it is imperative that we prepare to set our year for success.

__str__: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 1 :: What You See Is What You Get - Part 1
title: What You See Is What You Get - Part 1
description: In this message, Curt Landry teaches on the principle of What You See Is What You Get.  What we focus on is what will manifest in our life… we get what we look at.  Are you tired of competing with the seen and the unseen… the soulish nature and the spiritual nature battling against one another? Curt Landry walks us through scripture that teaches us how to use God’s Word and prayer to give the ‘control room’ of our mind victory over the natural, allowing us to see the promise that God is trying to plant within us.

__str__: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 1 :: Nothing New Under the Sun - Part 1
title: Nothing New Under the Sun - Part 1
description: "Nothing New Under the Sun?" is a message on identity. The Body of Christ is in a culture war, this has always been the case. Acts 19 is a perfect example of this, when Paul asks two very important questions as he spoke to the Believers in Ephesus..."Did you receive the Holy Spirit?" and "What were you baptized into?" These two questions are two of the very same questions denominations are asking to this day. The battle over the Holy Spirit and Baptism are two of top disagreements that the Church battles to this day. There is nothing new under the sun. Now is the time to put some blinders on and stay focused on the work that God has called you to do. Do not look to the identity of confusion and fear that the news is spreading, but stand fast on the Word of God, looking forward to what God WILL do for HIS name sake.
season: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: Speaking In Tongues - Part 1
title: Speaking In Tongues - Part 1
description: Speaking in tongues is a grace gift from God that is only beneficial during our earthly lives. Those who do not believe in tongues and do not operate in it are missing out on this temporary opportunity. This gift brings great power in that when we pray in the Holy Spirit, things change. We must not relegate speaking in tongues to religion or think it has died out, because it is still alive and well today. When we receive the Word of God and get born again, our very first experience as new Christians is receiving the Holy Spirit; the second experience is the baptism of the Holy Spirit with the evidence of speaking in tongues. These experiences were described in the book of Acts when several of the apostles ministered to the Samaritans. It is entirely possible to be a believer without the ability to speak in tongues, but receiving this gift changes our lives powerfully.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: No More Limits - Part 1
title: No More Limits - Part 1
description: There is no limit to what God can do in our lives, yet we can limit our lives by how we see ourselves. In the Old Testament, the children of Israel shrank back from claiming what God promised them because they saw themselves as inferior. Their thoughts and beliefs contradicted what God spoke about them through Caleb. This applies to us in that if we do not renew our minds to our identity in Christ, we limit ourselves. It is important that we do not view ourselves as ill-equipped, unable, inadequate, or insufficient. If we are to experience God in all his magnificence, we should see him as big as he is, and envision ourselves in the midst of his big plan. When we think this way, it allows God to accomplish the things he wants to do.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: Uncovering the Spirits of Mammon - Part 1
title: Uncovering the Spirits of Mammon - Part 1
description: The demonic spirit of mammon is very pervasive and subtle, and it can be difficult to detect unless we remain vigilant against it. This spirit is attached to money, and it tries to persuade us to trust money more than God. Wealth and riches cannot buy healing, deliverance, grace, or any other blessings from God; trust is the currency of the kingdom. Whether or not we are trustworthy is demonstrated in how we handle money, which God considers the least important thing. We can choose to either let the spirit of mammon dictate what we do with money or allow the Spirit of God to always tell us how to manage it. If we fail to make a choice, by default the spirit of mammon will govern us in this area. Therefore, we must be careful what spirit influences us when it comes to the financial realm.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: Speaking in Tongues - Part 2
title: Speaking in Tongues - Part 2
description: Speaking in tongues is a grace gift from God that is only beneficial during our earthly lives. Those who do not believe in tongues and do not operate in it are missing out on this temporary opportunity. This gift brings great power in that when we pray in the Holy Spirit, things change. We must not relegate speaking in tongues to religion or think it has died out, because it is still alive and well today. When we receive the Word of God and get born again, our very first experience as new Christians is receiving the Holy Spirit; the second experience is the baptism of the Holy Spirit with the evidence of speaking in tongues. These experiences were described in the book of Acts when several of the apostles ministered to the Samaritans. It is entirely possible to be a believer without the ability to speak in tongues, but receiving this gift changes our lives powerfully.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: A Grace Gift: Speaking in Tongues - Part 1
title: A Grace Gift: Speaking in Tongues - Part 1
description: Speaking in tongues while praying is a grace gift from God, but many people are not using this gift as they should.  There are two guidelines to remember as we talk to God through prayer. When we pray according to the finished works of Jesus, we should not ask God to do something He has already done.  When we were born again, we were already healed, delivered, prospered, and forgiven.  What we should pray for is wisdom, enlightenment, and revelation in the power and knowledge of Christ.

__str__: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 1 :: Rest In The Fire Of His Love - Part 1
title: Rest In The Fire Of His Love - Part 1
description: This message by Curt Landry, "Rest in the Fire of His Love" will clear up any confusion you may have over what it really means to enter God's Rest. Have you ever had confusion over prophetic words like 'wait,' 'stand still,' 'be still,' or 'rest?' Have you read scripture speaking of 'entering into His rest,' and said to yourself, 'what does that really mean?' Scripture tells us to REST when all around us there is turmoil and confusion – and our own soul speaks contrary to that 'rest.' We react to change and stress usually in a negative way – not a way of peace and rest. In this message Curt will give you keys to learn how and live in God's Rest. When you enter His rest, you will cease to do your own works and begin doing His works in His power. Don't let fearful thoughts and anxieties keep you from being consumed by the fire of His love. Don't let your hardships and trials keep you in the wilderness of fear, doubt, and unbelief. Stop nursing and rehearsing those fears and learn how to move into the love and mercy of God to trust Him that ALL things work together for your good because you are trusting in Him. Learn how to enter into His Rest today!
season: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 1

__str__: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 1 :: Parable of the Sower Explained - Part 1
title: Parable of the Sower Explained - Part 1
description: Your entire life is a parable of sowing seeds of time, task, and activities—you will reap what you sow. Change your seed—change your heart. Increase the quality of your life by understanding that you can sow better quality seed; the choice of how, when, and where you sow your seed has a direct impact on the quality of life you enjoy.
season: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 1

__str__: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 1 :: Faith and Hope - Part 1
title: Faith and Hope - Part 1
description:
"Faith and Hope," is a message by Curt Landry that will prepare you for promotion! The Lord wants His people to be overcomers, walking in great faith and with great hope in the One who accomplishes His purposes in us and through us. In this message, Curt Landry teaches on five major areas where the enemy tries to steal our faith and hope. Instead of being overcome by the enemy, Curt teaches how to apply faith and hope to BE the OVERCOMERS that God has called us to be.
As Curt takes you verse by verse through Hebrews 11 and 12, you will learn about these five 'attack zones' and how to avoid them. You will learn that your faith is the "substance of things hoped for." The Greek word for substance is defined as a title deed of guarantee. Faith is a 'title deed' to carry over your heart, so you can speak out the things you hope to see. Faith - the title deed of things hoped for. It’s your faith in the unseen that gives you the unwavering hope to overcome all fear and doubt. It’s by faith that you speak out His Word – you prophesy what you see by Faith as you Hope for the unseen things to come. Hope – hope is birthed in the Spirit, through prayer, supplication, proclamation and decrees. God creates with words spoken through people of faith, not people of doubt and unbelief. Take the title deed of your faith back! Learn to have a lifestyle of walking in faith, hearing from the Father, and speaking out the unseen in hope with the Father’s Love.
season: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 1

__str__: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1 :: Be Fair With One Another
title: Be Fair With One Another
description: Billy is really excited about entering a model boat in a boat-building competition. When he learns that Pops had built an award-winning boat for last year's contest, he borrows Pops' boat and enters it in the competition. The boat wins first prize, but Paula and Lisa help Billy understand that entering Pops' boat was breaking the rules and just wasn't fair to the others. Billy returns the prize money and learns a lesson about fairness and honesty.
season: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1

__str__: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1 :: Respect Others
title: Respect Others
description: Personal items are disappearing from the lab. Tools or equipment vanish from various workbenches. Later, some of these are returned but wind up in a different place. Dr. Wonder investigates and finds that Billy is borrowing things without the permission of the owner. Paula sprays Billy with a formula that will turn him invisible for 30 minutes. He soon finds out that he is not happy when people look right through him. He learns to respect other people and their things.
season: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1

__str__: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1 :: Trust God
title: Trust God
description: Lisa has a new desk. She asks Billy to put it together for her. Billy is happy to do it, but he doesn't think he needs to follow the designer's directions, so he tosses them aside. Later Lisa comes back to see how Billy is doing, but the desk is an absolute mess. Lisa explains why Billy should always follow the designer's directions. The one who created it knows more about the product than anyone else. Billy learns his lesson, follows the directions, and puts the desk together just the way it was supposed to be.
season: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1

__str__: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1 :: Sharing Can Be Fun
title: Sharing Can Be Fun
description: Dr. Wonder presents a new piece of equipment for the lab - a video camera. He explains that the equipment is very expensive and the lab can't afford for each person to have one, so they will all need to share this one. But Billy wants to use it all the time. This causes a problem in the lab, and Dr. Wonder has to resolve the issue by teaching Billy how important it is to share.
season: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1

__str__: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1 :: Don't Hold On To Anger
title: Don't Hold On To Anger
description: Billy is working on a project and it blows up over and over again. Finally, in disgust he loses his temper and smashes several things. Dr. Wonder teaches Billy about anger and helps him to understand how to channel his anger in positive ways. Billy learns how to control his anger and make it work for him, not against him.
season: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1

__str__: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1 :: Care For Others
title: Care For Others
description: One of Dr. Wonder's old friends is a magician. Dr. Wonder invites him to perform his act for the staff just before he leaves on a trip. The magician cannot take his pet rabbit with him, so he asks the staff to take care of the rabbit while he is away. But moments after he leaves for the airport, the rabbit has vanished. The whole staff looks and looks for the rabbit. Finally, they find him! He is in the arms of Pops at Dr. Wonder's desk. They are all relieved, and they realize it's very important to take good care of one another -- yes, even rabbits!
season: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1

__str__: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1 :: Obedience Is Important
title: Obedience Is Important
description: Pops and Dr. Wonder are working on a surprise—a new soft drink for the Finger Food Café. Dr. Wonder tells the staff not to go into his office until the project is finished. But one night Lisa goes into his office to straighten it up. She is so thirsty she drinks a green liquid sitting in a beaker on his desk. Her skin turns a bright green! Then Billy comes in and also drinks the liquid. When Dr. Wonder arrives, he sees the two green employees. Pops whips up an antidote and all is well, but they have learned a lesson about obedience!
season: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1

__str__: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1 :: Always Be Honest
title: Always Be Honest
description: Paula has a problem. Every time she turns on the water at the sink in her lab, it sprays her in the face. She asks around to find someone to fix the plumbing. Billy claims he can do it. But his solution is silly and doesn't work. It's obvious he knows nothing about plumbing, but lied about it because he wanted to impress everyone. The whole staff teaches Billy that lying destroys trust. Pops finally comes to the rescue to fix the sink, and Billy promises to be honest all the time.
season: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1

__str__: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1 :: Let Your Light Shine
title: Let Your Light Shine
description: There is a terrible thunderstorm and all the lights go out in the lab. While Lisa and Dr. Wonder go to try to repair the problem, Billy decides he can make his way around the lab in the dark. So Paula turns off her flashlight and lets Billy grope around in the dark. He trips over things and breaks things. When Dr. Wonder returns, he sees what a mess the lab is in. He helps Paula learn that if we don't let our light shine, people will just stumble around in the dark. And Billy learns to trust the light, not himself. We can fail. God will not.
season: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1

__str__: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1 :: Keep Your Promises
title: Keep Your Promises
description: Dr. Wonder promised to take his daughter to an afternoon baseball game. But Billy accidentally spills hot coffee on Lisa's back, and Dr. Wonder has to take her to the emergency room. When his daughter arrives at the lab, he is not there. She is upset that he broke his promise. On the way back home, she stops by the Finger Food Café and has a talk with Carlo. He helps her understand that sometimes things happen that we can't control and promises must be delayed. Soon Dr. Wonder shows up. He has adjusted his schedule so he can take his daughter to the game the following day. They head home together.
season: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1

__str__: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1 :: Never Give Up
title: Never Give Up
description: Dr. Wonder is working on a robot in the lab. He accidentally steps on a bad electrical cord and gets a nasty shock. He becomes like a robot. Billy, Paula and Lisa all try to help him come out of it, but everything they try fails. They feel like giving up, but they know they can't. They must never give up. Finally, Billy decides to discharge the electricity by grounding Dr. Wonder and placing a light bulb in his mouth. The bulb lights up instantly, but then it slowly dims. At last Dr. Wonder is back to normal! The robot gets fixed and does a little celebration dance.
season: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1

__str__: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1 :: You Are Precious
title: You Are Precious
description: Paula's husband and children come in to have lunch with her. Paula's mother has sent them a CD with some pictures of Paula when she was a little girl. The family enjoys looking at the pictures together, but they notice Paula sometimes looks sad. When the children ask why, she explains that because her family was all hearing, she usually felt left out. But later she learned how very precious she is to God and that made all the difference!
season: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1

__str__: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1 :: Be Responsible
title: Be Responsible
description: Billy fixes lunch and makes a mess in the microwave and on the break room table, but doesn't clean it up. Dr. Wonder finds the mess and explains to Billy that this is not being responsible. It's very important to be responsible for his things. God has given him many things, and he must be responsible and dependable. Billy cleans up the mess, and everyone is proud of him.
season: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 1

__str__: Dr. Wonder's Workshop :: 2 :: Bully for You
title: Bully for You
description: The first weekly Christian television series performed in ASL for deaf and hard-of-hearing children. Learn important lessons of faith and virtue with Dr. Wonder and all his friends on this unique, fun and educational kids' program. Dr. Wonder's Workshop is targeted toward deaf and hard-of-hearing children, but is also perfect for hearing children who can't speak because of illness or disability, people learning English as a second language, stroke victims, and educators who work with children.

description: Enjoy this special word of encouragement as Curt Landry shares about how to Protect Your Hope. Follow along in Proverbs 13:12 as Pastor Curt brings new understanding to “hope deferred makes the heart sick.”  He explains that developing a healthy heart that remains steadfast in the love of God is imperative to sustaining our faith in Him. Through this process, we will maintain a healthy heart that does not lose hope during difficult seasons of pruning.

description: This prophetic message by Curt Landry, "It's Time To Move On" will motivate you in your walk with the Lord to step out of your past in order to move into your future. When you face unsure circumstances in your life, you need to know that sometimes God closes doors because it's time to MOVE forward. He knows you won't move sometimes unless circumstances force you. __str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: The Ministry of the Holy Spirit - Part 2
title: The Ministry of the Holy Spirit - Part 2
description: To reconcile why the Holy Spirit was sent, we must study the Scriptures to understand His purpose. If we do not understand His ministry and how He operates in our lives, we could find ourselves believing a fable. The Spirit did not come to convict us of the things we do wrong or the mistakes we make; He came to convict us of unbelief in Jesus. This unbelief is the sin the Holy Spirit came to point out to us. Our mistake is focusing on the fruit of an issue, which are our actions, instead of on the root, which is our unbelief. We see this illustrated in the Bible when David’s doubt in what God told him caused him to commit adultery and murder, and when Moses’ doubt that God could bring water from a rock kept him from entering the Promised Land. When we understand the relationship between our unbelief and our actions, our behavior will radically change for the better.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: Exceeding Glory - Part 1a
title: Exceeding Glory - Part 1a
description: The Holy Spirit is the administrator of change in us. He can change us much better than we could ever change ourselves. There is a connection between the grace of God, which is the current covenant under which we operate, and the Holy Spirit. Although the Law of Moses has expired, many people still try to live under it. They do not have the Holy Spirit to guide them; for them, the law is still in effect. When we embrace the Word of God and remain in it, we are gradually transformed into God’s image; this is something that is impossible to do through self-effort. The Holy Spirit takes full responsibility for the changes that will take place in us. When we trust Him, we see a glorious transformation.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: Speaking in Tongues - Part 1a
title: Speaking in Tongues - Part 1a
description: Religion has a way of getting us to believe something without scriptural basis to support it. If we find ourselves believing a teaching that is nowhere to be found in the Scriptures, it might be time to re-evaluate that belief. Speaking in tongues is an example. There have always been people who mock speaking in tongues, but this is a valid spiritual gift that accompanies the baptism of the Holy Spirit. Some people think speaking in tongues ceased when the last apostle died, but this is a misunderstanding that stems from misinterpreting the Scriptures. The gift of tongues is still relevant and evident today, and it will continue for as long as we are on this earth. It is a powerful tool to help us bypass our intellect and pray the perfect prayer directly to God.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: A Grace Gift: Spreaking in Tongues - Part 1a
title: A Grace Gift: Spreaking in Tongues - Part 1a
description: Speaking in tongues is a grace gift from God that is only beneficial during our earthly lives. Those who do not believe in tongues and do not operate in it are missing out on this temporary opportunity. This gift brings great power in that when we pray in the Holy Spirit, things change. We must not relegate speaking in tongues to religion or think it has died out, because it is still alive and well today. When we receive the Word of God and get born again, our very first experience as new Christians is receiving the Holy Spirit; the second experience is the baptism of the Holy Spirit with the evidence of speaking in tongues. These experiences were described in the book of Acts when several of the apostles ministered to the Samaritans. It is entirely possible to be a believer without the ability to speak in tongues, but receiving this gift changes our lives powerfully.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: Communing with the Holy Spirit - Part 1a
title: Communing with the Holy Spirit - Part 1a
description: To commune with the Holy Spirit means to get to know Him intimately. This type of relationship is important, because He is the administrator of the new covenant of grace under which we live. In this covenant, we need to believe in Jesus and His finished work; the Holy Spirit guides us and helps us to do that. A relationship with Him involves two-way communication and fellowship, which includes praying in the Spirit to sharpen our awareness of when He is speaking to us. God wants to converse with us all the time, not just at church, and He wants to teach us things about life that we could never discern on our own. The covenant of grace has many layers to it, and we need the Spirit of grace to take us through each one. Speaking in tongues is a vital part of our union with Him, and this type of prayer brings us multiple benefits.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: Dimensions to Praying in the Spirit - Part 1a
title: Dimensions to Praying in the Spirit - Part 1a
description: In our prayer lives, praying in the Holy Spirit takes us to a deeper spiritual level than praying in our own language ever could. Praying in tongues bypasses our intellectual understanding, and brings us to the point where we must rely on inspiration from the Holy Spirit. Many churches do not teach about tongues because they do not understand it, but this is where the deeper manifestations of God begin. When we pray in this manner, not only are we depending on the Spirit to give us utterance, but we are also building up our spirits, our souls, and our physical bodies. In the New Testament we see Jesus, Himself, praying in the Holy Spirit during His most difficult and painful times. Groaning in the Spirit is one of the most powerful things Christians can do when we feel the need to pray but we do not know the right words. If we want to change the world, we begin by praying with groanings too deep for words in order to receive power from the Holy Spirit to successfully do so.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: From Condemnation to Grace - Part 1a
title: From Condemnation to Grace - Part 1a
description: The new covenant of grace is completely different from the old covenant of the law. Now that we are living under grace, we need to know what life is like under this covenant. The law was designed to reinforce the people’s guilt and constantly remind them of their shortcomings, but when Jesus came, He came to redeem and deliver, not to shame or punish. Most churches today seem to have forgotten this; instead of focusing on God’s favour toward us, they focus on telling us to keep the rules and uphold the standards of the law. Condemnation from the law is not a part of the new covenant, and if we feel condemned, that feeling did not come from God. The law heaps fear and shame on us, but grace offers us mercy, compassion, and forgiveness. Jesus had plenty of opportunities to condemn others, but instead of judging them, He forgave them and showed them grace. Faith in Christ transformed the lives of Zacchaeus as well as the woman caught in adultery, and it will change us as well.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: From Condemnation to Grace - Part 2a
title: From Condemnation to Grace - Part 2a
description: Jesus’ goal during earthly ministry was to demonstrate grace to people, not condemn them. Condemnation is not from God, but from Satan. It is far-reaching and deadly; every issue we encounter that causes us to struggle springs from condemnation. The enemy uses it against us because he has been judged guilty and condemned. He is now trying to pass his condemnation on to us. Every time we miss the mark, the devil is already ready to whisper that we are not good enough, not doing enough to please God, and are unable to be everything God wants us to be. The devil uses the ministry of condemnation to constantly throw our past mistakes in our faces and make us feel ashamed, guilty, and fearful. Freedom and true change the way God intends only comes by accepting and preaching the ministry of reconciliation, to remind ourselves and others of who we are and what we have in Christ.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: The New Covenant - Part 1a
title: The New Covenant - Part 1a
description: As born again people, we are no longer under the dispensation of the law, which was based on the Old (Mosaic) Covenant. We are now under the dispensation of grace, and we have access to a new and better covenant with better promises. Under the Old Covenant, man was required to keep the law and offer sacrifices to God in order to cover sins, which resulted in God’s blessing being released. Under the New Covenant, we are simply required to believe that God has forgiven our sins and been merciful toward us, and thank Him for His blessing that has been eternally released.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: Covenant of Promise - Part 1
title: Covenant of Promise - Part 1
description: Because of the current covenant of grace under which we now live, we do not have to struggle to get what we need to succeed. Everything has already been done and made available to us by the cross of Christ. However, to get Jesus’ finished works to manifest in our lives, we must respond to them in faith. This includes our salvation, deliverance, prosperity, forgiveness, and every other promise that God made.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: Covenant of Promise - Part 2a
title: Covenant of Promise - Part 2a
description: We can claim the promises for ourselves when we understand the spiritual laws He established. Not only is it important that we are aware of these laws, but we must also know that Christ has given us specific authority to enforce them. Regardless of who we are or what is going on in our lives, these spiritual principles will always work for us without fail if we believe them.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: Covenant of Promise - Part 2b

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: Covenant of Promise - Part 3a
title: Covenant of Promise - Part 3a
description: The difference between the Old Testament Abrahamic covenant and the new covenant of grace is that under the old covenant, no faith was needed to receive God’s promises. All that was necessary was to be a descendant of Abraham by blood. Under grace, belief in what Jesus did is the only requirement to receive the promises. This radically impacts every area of our lives. Under the old covenant, only certain people were eligible to be blessed; everyone else was excluded. Under grace, all who believe are blessed. Every division and limitation is erased in Christ, and we are equal in Him. The blood of Abraham is no longer necessary to inherit the blessings when we have the Spirit of Christ.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

title: The Good Fight - Part 1a
description: We are fighting a spiritual battle in our minds. We must remember that doubt and unbelief can stop a breakthrough coming our way. The world has many paths we can follow, but Jesus is the only true path. When we allow the Holy Spirit to operate in our lives we are granted wisdom from God to live successfully, through practical application, in this physical world.

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: Reacquainted with the Holy Spirit
title: Reacquainted with the Holy Spirit
description: There is a definite connection between the Holy Spirit and the grace of God, and we must understand the Spirit's work and His purpose on the earth. We have a tendency to get very absorbed in our own abilities and what we can do for ourselves. We can proverbially pat ourselves on the back and say, “We did that, we made this happen.” However, when we take an honest look at our lives, we must admit that there are some things that happen that defy all natural laws, things for which we cannot take credit. This is the Holy Spirit at work. Although He is a spirit, He is not “spooky” in the way we think of ghosts. He is one part of the triune God, and He is the one who empowers Christians to live Christian lives.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: How Not to be Tempted by Unbelief - Part 1a
title: How Not to be Tempted by Unbelief - Part 1a
description: As Christians, it always benefits us to practice the basics of biblical teachings. Our success or failure depends on us mastering these basics, one of which is the importance of avoiding unbelief. Abraham, known for his great faith, believed God when God made him a promise. The Bible is filled with promises God makes to us, and when we face situations in our lives, we have the same opportunity as Abraham to exercise our faith. Abraham and Sarah’s physical circumstances contradicted what God said, and so Abraham deliberately considered the promise, not the contradiction. We cannot be tempted by something we refuse to think about. Our minds are the arena of faith, and therefore, overcoming temptation and unbelief begins with our thoughts.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: How Not to be Tempted by Unbelief - Part 2a
title: How Not to be Tempted by Unbelief - Part 2a
description: Many contemporary Christians seem as if they do not know how to get manifestations of God’s promises. One example of a powerful manifestation is given to us in the Old Testament, when Abraham believed God despite overwhelming contradictory evidence in the natural realm. Abraham had a choice whether to focus on the physical situation or the supernatural promise; this applies to us today when we are faced with temptation. Like Abraham, we can successfully overcome temptation when we think about what God says to us more than what the world says to us. Temptation is pressure applied to the flesh, and as long as we consider the problem, the pressure will continue. However, we cannot be tempted by something we do not think about. To consider is to deliberate, ponder, or give attention to something; temptation loses its power over us when we refuse to examine or meditate on anything contradictory to God’s Word.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

title: Alignment: The Key to Living in Peace - Part 1
description: In Curt Landry’s message, “Alignment: The Key to Living in Peace”, he begins by speaking about the importance of coming in to agreement in real time. He then goes on to express the importance of alignment out of Zion. Curt Landry stresses that in the end times all the knowledge will come out of Jerusalem. The promises of God will come to pass. We have to understand that we must walk in the ways of the Lord, no matter the cost. Join the congregation as they gain greater understanding on how to walk in alignment with the covenant keeping God of Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, thereby experiencing peace that far passes worldly understanding.

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: Unbelief: How It Counteracts Faith - Part 1
title: Unbelief: How It Counteracts Faith - Part 1
description: On our Christian walk, faith in what God has made available to us is extremely important if we are to see any manifestations at all in our lives. Releasing our faith is a powerful tool in our fight against the unbelief the enemy sends against us. Self-effort is the opposite of trust in God, and if we find ourselves working to earn what we want to receive from Him, this is an indication that we are operating in unbelief. We must not confuse empty works with works of faith. There is technically nothing wrong with doing something in order to see the manifestations of God’s promises, as long as what we do is inspired by the Holy Spirit and led by Him. Doubt short-circuits our faith. When we struggle, we do not need more faith; we simply need to banish unbelief in our lives, in any degree and in any form in which it shows up.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

__str__: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 1 :: Key to Success - Part 1
title: Key to Success - Part 1
description: Curt Landry brings a fatherly word in this message, "Key to Success," for this is a personal message from the heart of a man through the heart of God that has affected him and taught him on his journey with family and friends. This is the story about the key to success that God wants to reveal in your life. In Joshua 1:8— one of the first scriptures the Lord gave to Curt—is the special word that begins the journey of this message. Do you know the difference between success and good success? We can prosper outside of God's will but at what cost? Stress, anxiety, fears, doubts....But, if we prosper inside God's will, His fruit is always pure and pleasant. It may still be hard work, but there—in God's heart—is not the confusion that man's fruit brings. Learn the foundation to God's "Key of Success." Learn how to focus on God's way of doing things instead of eating the bread of sorrows when you always give-in to your own way. Learn these essential truths in your walk with your Heavenly Father...Curt reveals a lifetime of experiences and wisdom that he has struggled through in his own life, before and after he was saved. Listen to his personal stories that led him to find God's wisdom and find how you can obtain the Key to success that God wants to give to you!
season: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: Grace Faith Balance - Part 1
title: Grace Faith Balance - Part 1
description: If we are not careful, we can take either faith or grace to the extreme. Paying too much attention to one without relating it to the other is harmful to us. Faith without corresponding actions is dead, but actions without faith can kill us. Without a solid understanding of the need to live in the balance between faith and grace, we can confuse the works of faith with works of the law.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

title: Living Under the Correct Covenant - Part 1a
description: Unlike the old agreement, the new covenant allows us to be blessed based on our status as born-again new creations in Christ. It is not about anything we do, but rather our decision to receive what Jesus has already done by faith.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1 :: Eradicating Sin Consciousness - Part 1
title: Eradicating Sin Consciousness - Part 1
description: Many Christians live a miserable life of guilt and condemnation. They do not accept God’s eternal forgiveness through Christ. They cannot even forgive themselves for their sins, and therefore they have sin consciousness (constantly reminding themselves of their wrongs). Furthermore, they believe their good deeds can make them right with God. To forgive ourselves and receive God’s forgiveness, we have to first believe that Jesus Christ has already made us right with God. Then we will be free to live a life of grace instead of living with sin consciousness.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 1

title: Eradicating Sin Consciousness - Part 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Comparing Covenants - Part 1
title: Comparing Covenants - Part 1
description: Life under grace is radically different than life under the Old Testament Law of Moses. The covenant of the law was about how well man performed, whereas the covenant of grace is about how well we believe Jesus performed. Although obedience is important under both covenants, obedience to the law has given way to obedience to the faith; this is something all Christians need to understand. Under the old covenant, the law kept us chained to our own performance but, under the covenant of grace, our faith in Jesus’ finished works frees us from our own inadequate efforts. Jesus is enough and He is all we need. All pressure is taken off what we do because the focus is now on what He did. We no longer need to earn God’s blessings because our trust in Jesus moves us into a position to receive the blessings that have already been made available.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Righteousness Without Works - Part 1
title: Righteousness Without Works - Part 1
description: When we examine the subject of grace, we must remember that it involves believing, not performing. However, it is incorrect to think that grace is a license to sin, because the objective of grace is still holiness. Accepting Jesus' finished works brings us from captivity and darkness to freedom and light. Because of what Christ did, we can call ourselves Christians. We no longer have to work to be righteous. Now, faith in Him makes us righteous.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Resilient Faith: Standing in Faith in a Dry Season - Part 1a
title: Resilient Faith: Standing in Faith in a Dry Season - Part 1a
description: There is a spiritual war going on and, as believers, we must deploy our faith in the midst of this spiritual battle. Faith requires patience, or being consistently the same, even in the midst of trouble. Our faith is challenged in times when it appears that the promises of God are not coming to pass. It is in these times that our ongoing belief and understanding the finished works available through God’s grace help us stand on His Word.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Equal in God's Eyes - Part 1a
title: Equal in God's Eyes - Part 1a
description: Jesus perfectly modeled grace during His earthly ministry so that people could see what love, compassion, and forgiveness look like. Letting Him, instead of the world, define gender roles liberates men and women while greatly enriching relationships. If we can understand just how much God values us and sees us in His plans, then we can live the life He wants for us and be the community that the world needs to see. In the garden of Eden, the enemy caused division between humanity and God. Jesus broke down the barriers between people so that we could all benefit by being one with Him. As believers, we can now live as equals, not as sinners living beneath our privileges.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: The Root Cause of Sin - Part 1a
title: The Root Cause of Sin - Part 1a
description: The Holy Spirit convicts us of sin, but He was not sent to convict us of wrong-doing. Most people think He focuses on our actions, but He actually was sent to convict us of unbelief. Sin is certainly wrong-doing, but every action of sin is a reaction of unbelief. When we are tempted to commit a sinful act, it indicates that there is some part of the Word of God that we do not believe. At the point of temptation, we must pause and locate the area of our unbelief. When we feel the pressure applied to us to doubt what God tells us, we must remember the example Jesus set when He faced the same temptations that we face, but did not give in to them. Our victory or defeat in life hinges on what goes on in our minds; when we choose to believe on Jesus, we can receive the same kind of life that He has.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: The Root Cause of Sin - Part 2a
title: The Root Cause of Sin - Part 2a
description: The root of all sin is unbelief in our identity in Christ. This unbelief can be traced all the way back to the garden of Eden. Adam and Eve did not realize who they were or that they were made to be just like God; therefore, Satan was able to lie to them and deceive them out of their identities. The resulting sin that they committed was born out of that unbelief. This is still true today. The three avenues where we can be tempted are the lust of the eyes, the lust of the flesh, and the pride of life. When we forget who we are in Christ, we are susceptible to falling prey to the enemy’s tricks when he tempts us in these areas. Our only hope of successfully resisting temptation is to base our identity in Jesus, who faced the same temptation as Adam and Eve but never for a moment forgot that He was the Son of God.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Overcoming a Hardened Heart
title: Overcoming a Hardened Heart
description: When our hearts are hardened, we lack spiritual wisdom, perspective, and understanding. Although we live in a physical world, Christians do not live as people following the dictates of society. We live and think on a higher level because we consider the Word of God.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: The Spirit of Grace - Part 1a
title: The Spirit of Grace - Part 1a
description: Most churches stay busy giving people rules and regulations to follow, but when we get saved, it is important to fall in love with Jesus. Many of the issues with which we struggle are the same ones He has already dealt with. We struggle because we focus too much on all the religious “do’s” and “don’ts” instead of focusing on Jesus. It is impossible to live Christian lives on our own; the Holy Spirit has a huge part in bringing us a life of grace. We cannot live sinless lives through self-discipline, and we are deluded if we think otherwise. The church is not a collection of perfect people, but rather a place where we admit we need Jesus. When we want to change for the better but cannot do so by ourselves, the Spirit of grace changes us from the inside out.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Overcoming a Hardened Heart - Part 1a
title: Overcoming a Hardened Heart - Part 1a
description: God has made available to us everything we will ever need in life. We access what we need by faith in what He has done; the spiritual laws that are in place allow us to do this. We should know that, as believers, we have the authority to use these laws by exercising our faith. The only thing that can stop us is a hardened heart. The danger in having a hardened heart is that, in this condition, we cannot activate God’s laws to work for us and we will not see manifestations. When the disciples were astonished to see Jesus walking on water immediately after watching Him perform a miracle feeding the multitudes with little food, their response was due to hardened hearts. We must be on guard against this spiritual state. Learning to trust God and what He says, instead of what we see in the natural realm, will keep us in constant expectation of the next supernatural miracle in our lives.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Overcoming a Hardened Heart - Part 1b
title: Overcoming a Hardened Heart - Part 1b
description: God has made available to us everything we will ever need in life. We access what we need by faith in what He has done; the spiritual laws that are in place allow us to do this. We should know that, as believers, we have the authority to use these laws by exercising our faith. The only thing that can stop us is a hardened heart. The danger in having a hardened heart is that, in this condition, we cannot activate God’s laws to work for us and we will not see manifestations. When the disciples were astonished to see Jesus walking on water immediately after watching Him perform a miracle feeding the multitudes with little food, their response was due to hardened hearts. We must be on guard against this spiritual state. Learning to trust God and what He says, instead of what we see in the natural realm, will keep us in constant expectation of the next supernatural miracle in our lives.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Overcoming a Hardened Heart - Part 2a
title: Overcoming a Hardened Heart - Part 2a
description: We all want to experience victory in our lives, but to see the results of what God said in His Word, we must consider His promises more than our situation. If we choose to focus on the problem instead, we harden our hearts to the promise. To consider something is to think about it, contemplate it, take it into account, or ponder it. Meditating on the Word gives us the results we want. Correspondingly, worrying about and meditating on the problem empowers it and blocks the manifestations of the promise. When situations arise in our lives, there is no reason to get stuck in them; we can simply go to the Word and find the specific promise that covers the issue. When we exercise authority over our emotions and thoughts, and deliberately focus on the Word, we see powerful results.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: The Heart: The Gateway to Life
title: The Heart: The Gateway to Life
description: It is important to receive God’s Word as seed, but it is equally important that we sow this seed in the right ground. Sowing seed in the wrong kind of ground will not produce a harvest. Every promise and finished work of God has been put inside the seed of His Word and reserved for us. If we want to see His promises come to pass in our lives, we must plant the Word in our hearts. As long as we take care to keep our hearts open and receptive to receive this seed, and we do not uproot it after it is planted, it is guaranteed to produce. In light of this, our hearts play a vital role in determining whether we experience change, or stay the same. We are free moral agents who can choose to plant the seed of God’s Word, or some other kind of seed, in our hearts, so the decision we make becomes vital in deciding the direction of our lives.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Jesus Our Redeemer - Part 1
title: Jesus Our Redeemer - Part 1
description: It took Jesus coming to free us from the consequences of inferiority, and of feeling inadequate and insecure. To free us from the sense of powerlessness, of unimportance. The scripture says in Romans 3:23 that all have sinned and fall short. In this message, Taffi Dollar shares how Jesus was sent to cover all our sins, insecurities and flaws.

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Who's The Boss? - Part 1a
title: Who's The Boss? - Part 1a
description:
Being the “boss” does not mean lording over others or sitting back waiting to be served; the scriptural definition of this is a willingness to serve and make sacrifices for others, like Jesus did. Servanthood based on biblical equality is not gender-based, but based on everyone submitting
one to another. Discover more of the benefits of living with a servant’s heart.

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Mutual Submission
title: Mutual Submission
description: The root of all sin is unbelief in our identity in Christ. This unbelief can be traced all the way back to the garden of Eden. Adam and Eve did not realize who they were or that they were made to be just like God; therefore, Satan was able to lie to them and deceive them out of their identities. The resulting sin that they committed was born out of that unbelief. This is still true today. The three avenues where we can be tempted are the lust of the eyes, the lust of the flesh, and the pride of life. When we forget who we are in Christ, we are susceptible to falling prey to the enemy’s tricks when he tempts us in these areas. Our only hope of successfully resisting temptation is to base our identity in Jesus, who faced the same temptation as Adam and Eve but never for a moment forgot that He was the Son of God.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Dealing With Your Emotions - Part 1
title: Dealing With Your Emotions - Part 1
description: Most people think that emotions cannot be controlled, but Christians have been given authority over our emotions. God gave us emotions as a gift, but we should not allow them to govern us or control our lives. Feelings of depression, rejection, or inferiority always have the potential to overwhelm us, but there is no reason to be emotionally out of control. The enemy uses our emotions to try to move us away from God’s will for our lives, so we must be vigilant against attacks in this area. When we find ourselves in a situation, we must not allow it to dictate how we feel. Instead of letting our emotions deal with us, we have the power to take charge and proactively deal with our emotions. Doing this gives us victory.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Taking Authority Over Your Emotions - Part 1
title: Taking Authority Over Your Emotions - Part 1
description: As believers, we have authority in many different areas, including our emotions. Our entire lives are based on whether we can control our emotions, or whether our emotions control us. We all have feelings, but letting them get the upper hand can cause problems. God designed us to master life, not to be mastered by it. We were made in God’s image, not just to reflect His love, but also to reflect His power and authority. God has a call on our lives, but we will not end up in the place He wants us to be, if we let our emotions dominate us. To fulfill His mission for us, we must take charge in this area.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Taking Authority Over Your Emotions - Part 2a
title: Taking Authority Over Your Emotions - Part 2a
description: We all experience emotions every day, but we do not need to allow them to move us away from God’s will for our lives. We have been given authority over our feelings; they do not have authority over us. The enemy is always plotting against us. One of his strategies is to attack our emotions. His goal is to get us away from being ruled by the Holy Spirit and move us toward being governed by our emotions. God wants us to master life, not for life to master us. We master life by refusing to allow our circumstances to dictate the way we feel. The battle we fight is in our minds, and we either win or lose, based on how well we exercise self-control over our emotions.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: The Spirit of Grace - Part 1b
title: The Spirit of Grace - Part 1b
description: Most churches stay busy giving people rules and regulations to follow, but when we get saved, it is important to fall in love with Jesus. Many of the issues with which we struggle are the same ones He has already dealt with. We struggle because we focus too much on all the religious “do’s” and “don’ts” instead of focusing on Jesus. It is impossible to live Christian lives on our own; the Holy Spirit has a huge part in bringing us a life of grace. We cannot live sinless lives through self-discipline, and we are deluded if we think otherwise. The church is not a collection of perfect people, but rather a place where we admit we need Jesus. When we want to change for the better but cannot do so by ourselves, the Spirit of grace changes us from the inside out.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: The Spirit of Grace - Part 2a
title: The Spirit of Grace - Part 2a
description: When we need grace, we cannot manufacture it through our own efforts; the Holy Spirit is the one who imparts unmerited, undeserved favor into our lives. We cannot live a life of grace without His help. The Holy Spirit is a real person and part of the Holy Trinity, not just a jump, a scream, or a physical outburst as defined by religion. Talking in tongues is certainly a manifestation of the Spirit, but He is much more than that. He is also a guide, a comforter, a teacher, a leader, and the one who administers the finished works of Jesus Christ into our lives. There are things that only the Holy Spirit can reveal to us that we will never know or be able to learn on our own. Trusting Him and welcoming Him into our lives takes us to a whole new level.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Gaining Control Over Your Emotions - Part 2a
title: Gaining Control Over Your Emotions - Part 2a
description: Historically, the church has devoted plenty of attention to spiritual things, but very little attention to emotions. Realistically, we must admit that we all have feelings; therefore, it makes sense to talk about them and learn how to deal with them. It is okay to have emotions, as long as they do not dominate us. God wants us to achieve emotional stability. This means asserting authority over our feelings and learning to fall “out of love” with our emotions. Real power and success comes from the ability to control our emotions, which is where the devil focuses his attacks. When we are aware of the enemy’s tactics, we can be on guard against all his efforts.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: The God of the Surprise - Part 2
title: The God of the Surprise - Part 2
description: God wants to be Lord over every area of our lives and He wants to make His presence known in amazing, astonishing ways. In order to do this, He is not above springing surprises on us when we least expect them. He did this with Mary when the angel announced she was to give birth to Jesus, and this completely changed her life. Likewise, when God reveals something surprising to us, our lives are also changed. He wants us to live in constant expectation and anticipation, and to be ready for miracles. This is the same God who redeemed us and bought us back from the bondage that resulted from Adam and Eve’s sin. Jesus paid the price to move us from sickness, poverty, and everything evil into health, prosperity at every level, and all that is abundantly good.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Put Your Foot Down - Part 1
title: Put Your Foot Down - Part 1
description: When we face uncertainty or unforeseen circumstances, we find the strength we need through God’s Word. We have been given authority over adversity, and we are not to allow situations to define us. We are not helpless, and it is important to see everything in our lives from God’s perspective. Regardless of the circumstances on the physical level, the enemy is still defeated and God is still good. Because of the finished works of Jesus, we won two thousand years ago. Although the devil is constantly plotting against us, God’s plan for us will prevail when we remember what the Word says. Once we put our foot down and decide to submit to God, Satan is forced to flee.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Biblical Equality Discussion
title: Biblical Equality Discussion
description: Biblical Equality is defined as everyone standing on equal ground, and it is achieved only through God’s influence. When God created Adam and Eve, he gave them the same amount of power and authority, with neither one dominating the other. Today, we all have an equal responsibility to obey God and operate in our highest potential. Equality is needed not just in society in general, but specifically in all our relationships. God has made the best of everything available to us, and this level of awareness will keep us from living beneath it.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

description: Brian Houston TV is a 30-minute television program filmed at Hillsong Church. Designed to help you live out your God-given potential. Pastor Brian Houston shares empowering and inspiring messages from the Word of God.
season: Brian Houston TV :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Mastering Your Emotions With Joy - Part 1
title: Mastering Your Emotions With Joy - Part 1
description: Our emotions can actually move our lives in a particular direction, either toward God’s will or away from it. As Christians, we must not become overly spiritual by pretending our feelings do not exist; they are real and they are an important part of our souls. God gave us emotions, but we must master them instead of allowing them to master us. Negative feelings move us away from the mission God has for us in life, but positive emotions like joy have the opposite effect. To succeed in life, we must learn to harness our emotions. Our feelings are determined by the way we think, whether godly or ungodly. Therefore, we must allow our thoughts to be controlled and directed by the Word of God.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Living By Faith, Not By Emotions - Part 1
title: Living By Faith, Not By Emotions - Part 1
description: One of the advantages we have as believers is that we have the Word of God as a resource to bring emotional stability to our lives. Mastering our emotions is impossible without His Word, and the world cannot do this because it does not have this resource. Without the wisdom gained from God, all we can do is simply cope with our feelings, and not let them dominate us. Living life by our emotions is bound to cause us to struggle. We must not base our feelings on our physical senses, because our emotions can change according to transitory appearances. True wisdom is letting our faith in God’s Word, instead of our feelings, govern our lives. Confidently knowing what He says to us in this area, instead of having to rely on our emotions at the moment, puts us in emotional control.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: The Great Exchange
title: The Great Exchange
description: Real change is not static; it is a transition and an ongoing process. It is facilitated by hearing the Word of God and being quick to adjust ourselves accordingly. Acknowledging God’s Word as the final authority gives us victory and causes us to experience success. We cannot help but be transformed as we spend time with God and continue to learn more about His character and nature. As Christians, we change a little each time He lovingly instructs us through reproof and discipline. His instruction moves us forward in our spiritual growth. Change is a way of life for the believer, and we must intentionally embrace it with no fear if we are to live changed lives.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Mastering Your Emotions With Peace - Part 1a
title: Mastering Your Emotions With Peace - Part 1a
description: God is a God of peace; He wants us to enjoy His peace in our own lives. Life has many interrelated moving parts, and whether we dominate it, or let it dominate us, depends on our emotional state of mind. God has already made peace available to us. Therefore, when we encounter situations that threaten to trigger negative emotions, we will know how to access this peace and stay in control of our feelings. This is not to say that stressful or unpleasant things will not happen to us. They will, but God has given us a way to deal with them and remain peaceful. His Word on how to use peace to master our emotions gives us the upper hand.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: The Grace to Change
title: The Grace to Change
description: Periodically, we must examine and identify areas of our lives where we need to make changes. This allows us to consider situations from a new perspective. We can actually limit what God can do for us if we do not allow His Word to transform us. Some things that happen in our lives are the result of wrong-believing, and shining the light of change in these areas helps us to believe correctly and get good results. We no longer have to stay the same; we have been empowered to rise to new levels. We do this by spending time in the Word, which frees us and destroys strongholds that previously kept us in bondage. Therefore, change should be a way of life for believers.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: How to Get Manifestation - Part 1a
title: How to Get Manifestation - Part 1a
description: Intellectually, we already know the importance of living in the proper balance of grace and faith. However, it is not enough simply to have head knowledge that by grace we are already healed, delivered, prosperous, and sound. It is not good to realize that these things have been made available to us, yet be unable to access them. Just like the right mix of sodium and chloride makes salt and adds flavor to our food, the right mix of grace and faith adds manifestations to our lives. It is time for Christians to know how to walk in the manifestations of what grace has provided. We do that by avoiding the extremes of leaning too far toward either grace or faith. Because of the finished works of Jesus, all we need to do to experience God’s glory is to employ our faith in what He did.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Causes of Depression and How to Get Out of It - Part 1
title: Causes of Depression and How to Get Out of It - Part 1
description: Our feelings, and how to deal with them, is a topic very few churches address. We all have emotions; however, it is important that our emotions do not have us. Because God has given us emotional control, we are in error if we think we cannot help the way we feel. Ignoring negative emotions is not the answer. To succeed in life, we must learn how to acknowledge them as they surface and speak the Word of God over them. This reinforces our authority over them and keeps them from spilling over when they should be contained. In this way, we can master our emotions the way God wants us to.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Steps Out of Depression
title: Steps Out of Depression
description: Depression can be described as emotional distress, and it is not God’s will for us. It is a sickness we do not need to tolerate because Jesus has already healed and redeemed us from it. Specifically, He went to the cross and paid the ransom to spare us from depression. God wants us to be healthy on all levels, including in our souls, where our feelings are located. When we feel negative emotions, we master them by resisting them and not allowing them to gain a foothold in our minds. We do this by standing on our believer’s authority, employing our faith in the Word, and giving praise and thanksgiving for what God has done for us. In this way, we escape depression and maintain our emotional stability.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: How to Overcome Stress - Part 1a
title: How to Overcome Stress - Part 1a
description: In these last days, God is poised to do supernatural things in our lives. However, stress is an enemy to the supernatural manifestations He wants for us. It is deadly to us in the spiritual realm, and it also causes emotional and physical health problems. As Christians, we must view stress as being as dangerous to our well-being as a net is to a bird. The Word of God shows us how to beat this emotion when it gets the best of everyone else. Stressful situations are bound to show up occasionally; however, remembering what God says about them helps us to overcome any accompanying fear or panic and to remain calm. Using the Word as a weapon against stress keeps us steady and prepared for the inevitable.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: How to Overcome Hurt - Part 1a
title: How to Overcome Hurt - Part 1a
description: Everyone has emotions, and everyone at some point in time will experience hurt. We live in a world filled with hurting people, and hurt people tend to say hurtful things to others. Unkind, cruel words from others can hurt us inside; hurt feelings rob us of God’s blessings. The potential for getting our feelings hurt is real, and the enemy wants to bring us to a place where we do not want to deal with this painful emotion. However, God’s will is for us to be delivered and healed from negative emotions. As born-again Christians, we know hurt must be dealt with immediately. The Word teaches us how to handle it when it happens. Using the believers’ authority we have over our feelings allows us to let go of the emotional pain and move on with our lives.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

title: How to Overcome Hurt - Part 1b
description: Everyone has emotions, and everyone at some point in time will experience hurt. We live in a world filled with hurting people, and hurt people tend to say hurtful things to others. Unkind, cruel words from others can hurt us inside; hurt feelings rob us of God’s blessings. The potential for getting our feelings hurt is real, and the enemy wants to bring us to a place where we do not want to deal with this painful emotion. However, God’s will is for us to be delivered and healed from negative emotions. As born-again Christians, we know hurt must be dealt with immediately. The Word teaches us how to handle it when it happens. Using the believers’ authority we have over our feelings allows us to let go of the emotional pain and move on with our lives.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Giving in Partnership and Fellowship - Part 1
title: Giving in Partnership and Fellowship - Part 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: How to Get Manifestation - Part 2b
title: How to Get Manifestation - Part 2b
description: Intellectually, we already know the importance of living in the proper balance of grace and faith. However, it is not enough simply to have head knowledge that by grace we are already healed, delivered, prosperous, and sound. It is not good to realize that these things have been made available to us, yet be unable to access them. Just like the right mix of sodium and chloride makes salt and adds flavor to our food, the right mix of grace and faith adds manifestations to our lives. It is time for Christians to know how to walk in the manifestations of what grace has provided. We do that by avoiding the extremes of leaning too far toward either grace or faith. Because of the finished works of Jesus, all we need to do to experience God’s glory is to employ our faith in what He did.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: The Number One Enemy to God's Favor - Part 1a
title: The Number One Enemy to God's Favor - Part 1a
description: In these last days, God’s righteousness is more visible than ever before. All over the world, people are being enlightened to the gospel of Grace. It is being widely preached, and the coming revival of God’s abundant grace will be like nothing we have ever seen. The ministry of righteousness is the ministry of the Spirit who guides us into the truth that when we are born again, we become God’s children, like our Brother, Jesus Christ. The Bible tells us that when we are in Christ and he is in us, we are just like him. Religion tells us otherwise, and it takes faith on our part to accept and believe this truth. The only thing stopping us from believing it is our wrong behavior motivated by our doubt.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: The Number One Enemy to God's Favor - Part 2
title: The Number One Enemy to God's Favor - Part 2
description: As Christians, we cannot position ourselves in the place where God wants to favor us when we operate in self-effort and pride. Pride is when we think we can rely more on what we do than on what Jesus did. But no matter how much we pray, how hard we try, or how many deeds we accomplish through our own performance, it does not come close to what Jesus and his blood accomplished on the cross. We cannot be perfected by our works, but only by the Spirit of God. In light of this, we must decide for ourselves if we will try to accomplish what Jesus already accomplished by trusting in our own performance, or if we will celebrate his already finished works. The manifestations of everything we could ever want or need depend on our faith in his ability.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: The Authority of the Believer - Part 1a
title: The Authority of the Believer - Part 1a
description: Through unmerited, undeserved favor, God has given us authority to do the same things that Jesus did during His earthly ministry. Those things include supernatural acts like healing the sick, raising the dead, and casting out demons. We may see ourselves as ordinary people, but if we are to use this authority we have been given, we must change the way we see ourselves. This power is given to every born-again Believer through God’s love and grace.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Do I Have to Confess My Sins to be Forgiven? - Part 2
title: Do I Have to Confess My Sins to be Forgiven? - Part 2
description: When we wrestle with the question of whether we must confess our sins for God to forgive us, we should remember that Jesus already offered us forgiveness two thousand years ago. The assumption that we must confess our sins, first, tells us that forgiveness depends on our own efforts. Forgiveness is part of the finished works of Jesus, but most Christians think they are required to continually confess their sins. Their fear is that if they do not do this, they will not have fellowship with God and they might die with unconfessed sin. A true understanding of His forgiveness reveals that He has already dealt with our sins. There is always a place for confession but, for believers, this should never be an attempt to get our sins forgiven. We confess and speak openly to our heavenly Father because we are already forgiven.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2
