title: Blinded by Love
description: Sabrina Greenlee's boyfriend and his secret girlfriend threw a cup of acid at Sabrina, which melted her face and left her near death. She woke to the realization that she was completely blind and her life would be forever changed. She believes she has survived to tell her story to help others survive.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: It's Never Too Late - Part 2
title: It's Never Too Late - Part 2
description: On this show, we’re talking with a couple who have been through tragedy after tragedy in their lives and in their marriage…yet they are still holding on to a thread of hope that they can overcome their circumstances together. One of them is ready to move forward hand-in-hand, but the other is about to give up hope. They are here, together, to receive counseling, and find out if they have reached the point of no return.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

title: Real Life Transformation
description: As a born again believer, you should be experiencing transformation in your life. season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Real Life Transformation
title: Real Life Transformation
description: As Christians, we must protect our belief system. If we believe the right things, we can live right; but if we believe wrong, we’ll live wrong.  When we are born again, we become new creatures in Christ. Our identity immediately changes from the carnal to the spiritual, and is based in Him from that point onward. Even when we sin, our behavior can never change who we are. If no one reveals the truth to us, then we will continue to believe a lie. Therefore, constantly renewing our minds with the Word reinforces the truth of who we are in Christ, and causes it to take root inside us.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: The Power of Sonship
title: The Power of Sonship
description: Christians have been called to be holy, which means living in the world without being part of it. As God’s sons, we are to live in the physical realm while operating in the supernatural realm. When we live above the natural, we live according to God’s spiritual laws that allow us to experience perpetual blessings. Most people do not understand the significance of being created in the image of God, Himself; they think they are “mere humans.” Thinking like this actually limits and hinders us from experiencing the supernatural life God wants for us. This kind of life is possible when we accept our identity in Christ. Doing this allows us to tap into the supernatural power of being God’s sons.

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1 :: Kingdom Men Rising: Lame Man Walking
title: Kingdom Men Rising: Lame Man Walking
description: (Acts 3:1-10) Lameness can come in all shapes and sizes. Even if you may be able to walk or run, you could still be mentally, politically or spiritually lame if you find yourself relying on others to do what you should be doing yourself. Tony Evans says there are far too many men failing to stand up on their own two feet and fulfill their responsibilities that God placed before them. Experience what it means to stop depending on others in order to man-up where you should stand-up.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1 :: Divine Encounters - Part 1
title: Divine Encounters - Part 1
description: (Exodus 3:1-14): One of the greatest encounters with God in the Bible is the story of Moses and the burning bush. But the thing that caught Moses’ eye was not merely the fire itself, but that the fire was not consuming the bush on which it dwelt. In this lesson on Moses’ divine encounter with God, experience how He can speak to you through the use of a contradictory situation.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1 :: Divine Encounters - Part 2: Encountering the Power of God
title: Divine Encounters - Part 2: Encountering the Power of God
description: (Exodus 14:1-23): When you find yourself facing a dilemma, you feel like you’re in a dead-end situation—that is, you’re between a rock and a hard place. The Israelites wound up in a dilemma when they found themselves between the Red Sea and an Egyptian army. In this lesson on one of the most noted stories in Israel's history, experience the kind of divine encounter with God that happens in the midst of a dilemma.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Overcoming Strife - Part 1
title: Overcoming Strife - Part 1
description: Many people think that through their works they will eventually earn their righteousness and holiness; the truth is that we are immediately made holy and righteous when we are born again. We can have peace of mind in the knowledge that our salvation rests in what Jesus did, not on anything we do.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Spiritual Blindness - Part 2
title: Spiritual Blindness - Part 2
description: Being spiritually blind to the Gospel of Grace can be compared to a physically blind person standing in a bright light but unable to see it. If we are spiritually blind, we will be subject to our natural senses to guide us through life. We will be controlled by our emotions, and our doubts and fears will muffle the voice of the Holy Spirit.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: The Power of Sonship - Part 2a
title: The Power of Sonship - Part 2a
description: When we find ourselves in trouble, it may be because we lack the godly wisdom to properly handle the issue. Asking God for His Word of understanding is the proper response to the situation. If we want control over our lives and victory over bad situations, we must understand that we are not ordinary human beings. If we have been born again, our identity has changed from servants to sons of God. Acknowledging our divine nature in God gives us the authority He wants us to walk in.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: The Power of Sonship - Part 2b
title: The Power of Sonship - Part 2b
description: When we find ourselves in trouble, it may be because we lack the godly wisdom to properly handle the issue. Asking God for His Word of understanding is the proper response to the situation. If we want control over our lives and victory over bad situations, we must understand that we are not ordinary human beings. If we have been born again, our identity has changed from servants to sons of God. Acknowledging our divine nature in God gives us the authority He wants us to walk in.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: The Power of Sonship - Part 1
title: The Power of Sonship - Part 1
description: As God’s sons, we are to live in the physical realm while operating in the supernatural realm. When we live above the natural, we live according to God’s spiritual laws that allow us to experience perpetual blessings. This kind of life is possible when we accept our identity in Christ. Doing this allows us to tap into the supernatural power of being God’s sons.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Overcoming Strife - Part 2a
title: Overcoming Strife - Part 2a
description: Strife brings with it the spirit of division, which is something we do not want in our lives. It can show up in many different ways to create confusion and steal our peace, and it is so devious that sometimes we can be unaware that we are operating in it. However, the Word of God gives us practical ways we can have victory over strife.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Trusting God with Your Finances - Part 1a
title: Trusting God with Your Finances - Part 1a
description: There is a connection between our faithfulness in handling money and our success in other areas of our lives. Our money management habits speak volumes about our character. When we refuse to let the evil spirit of mammon influence us and can prove ourselves trustworthy with money, we position ourselves for blessings in every other area of our lives.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1 :: Divine Encounters - Part 3: Encountering God's Promise
title: Divine Encounters - Part 3: Encountering God's Promise
description: (Genesis 22:1-18): Has it ever felt like God did not keep His promises? Though we know He cannot lie, there still exist instances where what He said and what you see do not seem to add up. When God asked Abraham to sacrifice his son Isaac, He was asking him to give up the very thing that God had promised. In this lesson, discover how when God wants to give you an encounter with Him, it just might come with a test for you to pass.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1

__str__: Jerry Savelle Ministries :: 1 :: Increasing Your Level of Expectation - Part 2
title: Increasing Your Level of Expectation - Part 2
description: Jerry Savelle teaches the uncompromising Word of God in down-to-earth terms, applicable to your life, dreams, and destiny. Discover through God's Word how you can be a victorious winner in life.
season: Jerry Savelle Ministries :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Works vs. Faith - Part 1
title: Works vs. Faith - Part 1
description: Faith, not our actions, is the victory that overcomes the world. Therefore, Christians must be careful not to belittle the importance of believing. If we believe strongly enough, eventually that belief will give birth to action. Without a solid understanding of the need to live in the balance between faith and grace, we can confuse the works of faith with works of the law.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Trusting God with Your Finances - Part 1b

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1 :: Divine Encounters - Part 4: Encountering God's Provision
title: Divine Encounters - Part 4: Encountering God's Provision
description: (1 Kings 17:8-16): Have you ever experienced a time where God didn’t come through when you needed Him to? Tony Evans says there are several reasons why God allows His people to enter into circumstances where provision is lacking. Learn how when we abandon God and look to our own resources, we end up blocking the provision that God wants to give to us and through us.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Trusting God with Your Finances - Part 2b
title: Trusting God with Your Finances - Part 2b
description: If we want breakthrough in our lives, any progress we experience is tied to our trust in God where giving is concerned. Most people who have the wrong idea about money do not understand the link between money and trust. The true currency in the kingdom of God is trust; when we understand this, we will find ourselves in a position to receive the blessings that Jesus’ finished works made available to us.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

title: Grace - A Round Table Discussion, Part 2a

season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Righteousness by Grace - Part 2
title: Righteousness by Grace - Part 2
description: It is a misunderstanding to think that grace is a license to sin, however, because holiness is still the objective of grace. Accepting His finished works brings us from captivity and darkness to freedom and light. Because of what Christ did, we can call ourselves Christians. We no longer have to work to be righteous because, now, faith in Him makes us righteous.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Works vs. Faith - Part 2
title: Works vs. Faith - Part 2
description: Faith, not our actions, is the victory that overcomes the world. Therefore, Christians must be careful not to belittle the importance of believing. If we believe strongly enough, eventually that belief will give birth to action. Without a solid understanding of the need to live in the balance between faith and grace, we can confuse the works of faith with works of the law.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Do We Really Need God? - Part 1a
title: Do We Really Need God? - Part 1a
description: The world operates by its own set of secular humanism principles, which teaches that everything is up to us and our own performance; it tells us to doubt God and not to depend on Him because He will let us down. This is a deception. What we need is not humanism or religion, but a deep relationship with God.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 ::  Do We Really Need God? - Part 2b
title: Do We Really Need God? - Part 2b
description: Secular humanism is the world exalting the "self-made man." However, anything good that happens to us is by God's grace and mercy, not by our own performance. Failure to acknowledge this is sheer arrogance. To achieve any level of success at all, we need God.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Real Life Transformation
title: Real Life Transformation
description: Jesus is Grace; therefore, He is the truth that brings us real freedom. Jesus accepts us as we are, but His intention is to transform us. When we believe what He says about our identity, we will experience real life transformation.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 2 :: The Passover of Our Heritage Part 2: Responsibility & Wisdom for Increase
title: The Passover of Our Heritage Part 2: Responsibility & Wisdom for Increase
description: Curt Landry Media is a platform for like-minded Believers, both Jew and Gentile, to gather together and grow in the richness of the heritage of our faith. We have a special focus on studying the roots of Christianity including Israel and prophecy. We believe that honour is a force and we treat each person with a level of value and respect that allows us to take the role of a servant in the relationship. We believe that God’s truth has the power to set people free, and we do everything in our power to remain faithful to His truth, in thought, in word, and in deed. We adhere to biblically based moral and ethical principles, and maintain these principles both in public and in private.
season: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 2

__str__: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 2 :: Developing King Priest Character
title: Developing King Priest Character
description: As you desire to walk in God’s highest and best, learn how to let God develop within you His King Priest Character as Curt Landry teaches in this message entitled, “Developing King Priest Character.” The King Priest Character is not something that you arrive at, but an attribute that you desire and aspire to. Curt teaches how to stay focused and on track in this desire to help you learn to allow that special purpose—the purpose God has for you—to develop within your identity. As Curt lays out strategic keys in this message, he unfolds specific skills to give you clear understanding of how you can walk in God’s best for your life.
season: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 2

__str__: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 2 :: Life Lessons You Should Know Sooner Than Later
title: Life Lessons You Should Know Sooner Than Later
description: In this personal reflection, Curt Landry shares ten "Life Lessons You Need to Learn Sooner Than Later." In this seasonal time of the counting down of the Omer—the time between Passover and Shavuot (Pentecost)—these personal reflections are life lessons that will be worth learning and applying to your life. As you grow older, you may see that you cannot achieve the hopes and dreams of younger days. But as Curt shares what he has learned over the years of his life—through the struggles and the victories—he unwraps within them profound messages for your life, today! Messages that hold the love of the Father who has a plan and a purpose for your life.
season: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 2

description: (Genesis 32:24-32): For you to have a divine encounter with God, there is a process that must first take place. Tony Evans says that until you become stripped of your self-sufficiency, God often remains a distant concept instead of a dynamic reality. If you’re still waiting on a spiritual breakthrough, learn the importance of giving up your independence to enable you to experience a new level of His reality.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Do We Really Need God? - Part 4a
title: Do We Really Need God? - Part 4a
description: Statistics show an increasing percentage of atheists who were formerly Christians, but walked away from God. This is due to a widespread misconception about who He is and what He is really like. When we realize that He is our heavenly Father who deeply loves us and wants a personal relationship with us, we can position ourselves to receive the good things He wants to give us.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: Freedom From the Heart - Part 1
title: Freedom From the Heart - Part 1

When we see God through the lends of Jesus, we will no longer fear Him.

__str__: Jerry Savelle Ministries :: 1 :: The Prayer of Petition - Part 1
title: The Prayer of Petition - Part 1
description: When God’s people pray, they want answers. Yet many Christians don’t know how to pray both effectively—in a way that gets results— and humbly—in a way that aligns with God’s will. Prayer is a powerful weapon against the true adversaries of God’s people: principalities, powers, dark rulers and spiritual wickedness in high places. These forces are the perpetrators of all kinds of evil: Addiction, abuse, poverty and spiritual bondage run rampant through families, churches, cities and nations. What can believers do to battle these forces? They can pray.

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: How to Wait for God - Part 1a
title: How to Wait for God - Part 1a
description: Specifically, there is a difference between “waiting for God” and “waiting on God.” To wait for God is to expect something good from Him; this involves patience. Waiting on God suggests the mindset of a waiter or servant. Waiting for Him involves courage, and is never a waste of time. It is especially important for us to know how to wait for God and look to Him, instead of relying on human aid, when trouble hits.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: The Art of Being Alone with God - Part 3a
title: The Art of Being Alone with God - Part 3a
description: Most problems that we encounter are resolved through a personal relationship with God; we develop this relationship by practicing the art of being alone with Him. We can actually choose how much alone time we have with God. If we let worldly clutter give us a noisy spirit, we will not hear Him when He talks to us. We must make knowing God our top priority, because everything in our lives flows from this intimate relationship.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2

__str__: Jerry Savelle Ministries :: 1 :: Count it all Joy - Part 1
title: Count it all Joy - Part 1
description: Dr. Savelle's daughter, Jerriann shares how we can be joyful when we're going through life's struggles big and small. The answer is Jesus. season: Jerry Savelle Ministries :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 2 :: The Contrast - Part 1a
title: The Contrast - Part 1a
description: Under the law, man had to perform to be blessed; now, all we need to do is to have faith in what Jesus has already done. We do not have to be aware of sin, because we are now free to be mindful of what Jesus' finished works made available to us. God has said we are righteous, redeemed, delivered, and healed. To receive these gifts, all we need to do is to believe this.

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1 :: Igniting Kindgom Prayer - Part 4: Praying in Jesus’ Name
title: Igniting Kindgom Prayer - Part 4: Praying in Jesus’ Name
description: (John 16:23-27): In the book of John, Jesus states whenever you ask for something in His name that you will receive it. But if you were to ask any believer if they’ve ever had a prayer go unanswered, their response would be yes. Tony Evans says this is because we often use His name in our prayers illegitimately. In this message, learn how to properly utilize the phrase “in Jesus’ name” as you begin to see prayers answered like never before.

description: (Luke 7:1-10): You can count on one hand the number of times in the Bible that Jesus marveled at someone’s actions. __str__: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 2 :: God's Times and Season
title: God's Times and Season
description: Join Curt Landry as he brings this powerful message: "God's Times and Season." Are you ready to come before God's throne of grace to receive a powerful word from the Lord? A once in a lifetime visitation? Are you prepared to receive all that God has prepared for you? Curt gives keys to help you unlock how to prepare for God's provisional blessings… knowing God's times will point to the season you are in for His glory! "How can I get in alignment with God for my visitation?", "What is God's purpose for me in His times and in this season?", "How do I activate His grace and His glory for this season?". Put yourself in God's times—station yourself in this season to receive all that God desires for you! What has been done in heaven is now traveling the earth for those who will receive it. Get ready to receive the outpouring of His Spirit and receive a fresh word from the Lord at Shavuot! "Shavuot is the empowerment take-off spot!" Learn how to prepare… and get ready to receive God's grace that aligns you with the Holy Spirit to receive His instruction that empowers you to apply His Word in each of His times and in each season of your life!
season: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 2

__str__: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 2 :: Keys to Empowered Prayer
title: Keys to Empowered Prayer
description: Curt Landry Media is a platform for like-minded Believers, both Jew and Gentile, to gather together and grow in the richness of the heritage of our faith. We have a special focus on studying the roots of Christianity including Israel and prophecy. We believe that honour is a force and we treat each person with a level of value and respect that allows us to take the role of a servant in the relationship. We believe that God’s truth has the power to set people free, and we do everything in our power to remain faithful to His truth, in thought, in word, and in deed. We adhere to biblically based moral and ethical principles, and maintain these principles both in public and in private.
season: Curt Landry Weekly Teaching :: 2

title: Igniting Kindgom Prayer - Part 6: The Kingdom Power of Prayer
description: (James 5:13-18): For many believers, the act of prayer has slowly devolved into a mere tradition that has no lasting impact on their lives. title: Igniting Kingdom Prayer - Part 9: Praying to Move Mountains
description: (Mark 11:20-26): We’ve all faced mountains throughout our lives—situations that loom so large you can’t find a way over or through it. Well, Jesus tells us we have the power to move these mountains, but many Christians wind up placing a lot of faith in the wrong things. In this message, Tony Evans discusses how prayer and just the smallest amount of faith in the right thing can set you free from the mountains that hold you hostage.

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1 :: Igniting Kingdom Prayer - Part 10: Prayer and Spiritual Warfare
title: Igniting Kingdom Prayer - Part 10: Prayer and Spiritual Warfare
description: (Ephesians 6:10-18): If you keep a spare tire in the back of your car, you’ll know that it’s only kept there for when something goes flat. Tony Evans says many Christians treat prayer like a spare tire—if nothing’s going flat in life, there’s no need for it. But the Bible says to pray at all times, and in this message, you’ll find that by doing so you’re preparing yourself for the inevitable occurrence of any spiritual warfare that may strike.

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1 :: Igniting Kingdom Prayer - Part 11: Praying Through a Crisis
title: Igniting Kingdom Prayer - Part 11: Praying Through a Crisis
description: (John 11:1-44): Whether you see it coming from far away or it just hits you out of nowhere, finding yourself face-to-face with a crisis is the kind of unwelcome experience nobody wants to be in. But in the midst of the financial, medical or mental chaos, Dr. Evans is here to remind you to ask yourself a very important question: “How can my crisis bring God glory?” In this lesson, be reminded of God’s power and ability to turn even the darkest of circumstances into that which will bring Him praise like you never could have imagined.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1 :: The Best of Tony Evans 2019: Lame Man Walking
title: The Best of Tony Evans 2019: Lame Man Walking
description: (Acts 3:1-10): Lameness can come in all shapes and sizes. Even if you may be able to walk or run, you could still be mentally, politically or spiritually lame if you find yourself relying on others to do what you should be doing yourself. Tony Evans says there are far too many men failing to stand up on their own two feet and fulfill their responsibilities that God placed before them. Experience what it means to stop depending on others in order to man-up where you should stand-up.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 3 :: January 1, 2020: Morality vs. The Mosaic Law - Part 4
title: January 1, 2020: Morality vs. The Mosaic Law - Part 4
description: To see the manifestations of what God has promised us, we simply need to believe Him. The confusion over what to have faith in began in the garden of Eden, when Adam and Eve ate from the wrong tree. The result was that they had faith in their own efforts to provide for themselves, instead of in God; this mindset still continues today.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 3

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 3 :: January 3, 2020: Are You of the Works of the Law or Are You of Faith? - Part 1a
title: January 3, 2020: Are You of the Works of the Law or Are You of Faith? - Part 1a
description: Living under the grace that came by Jesus requires belief in what He has done. This even extends to what we say; although our words carry great weight, what we declare will never be more powerful than what Jesus already did. This means that we no longer have to live based on what we do; we are now free to live based on what Jesus did, and our belief in that.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 3

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 3 :: January 5, 2020: The Art of Being Alone with God - Part 1a
title: January 5, 2020: The Art of Being Alone with God - Part 1a
description: Trusting in the Lord and waiting on Him allows the Holy Spirit to lead us out of whatever situation we are facing. When trouble shows up, seeking God and ignoring the noise and clutter of the world allows Him to clearly instruct us on how to proceed. As Christians, we must practice the art of getting alone with Him.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 3

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1 :: Best of Tony Evans 2019: Jesus the Great I Am
title: Best of Tony Evans 2019: Jesus the Great I Am
description: (John 8:48-59): When Moses asked God what He wanted to be referred to as to the Israelites, God responded: "I Am." But what does the name I Am even mean? Jesus uses this name for Himself indicating that He is God. In this lesson, Tony Evans explains that this name is more than just a name—it defines a personal God who is who He declares Himself to be.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1 :: Don't Miss Christ this Christmas - Part 1
title: Don't Miss Christ this Christmas - Part 1
description: (Luke 2:1-7): On the night that Christ was born, there are a number of people who missed the greatest birth of all time because they were either too busy or refused to acknowledge it. Well, in order to help prevent you from making the same mistake, Tony Evans takes a look at each of those people on that fateful night as he reminds you not to overlook the reason for the season.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1 :: Best of Tony Evans 2019: Divine Coincidences
title: Best of Tony Evans 2019: Divine Coincidences
description: (Esther 5–6): Contrary to popular opinion, there is no such thing as luck. Rather, what appears to be a coincidence is actually God’s providence combined with His divine timing. Using the story of Esther, Tony Evans demonstrates how God puts all the pieces of the puzzle together to prepare us for "such a time as this."
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 1

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2 :: Let Go(d): Trusting God in a Storm
title: Let Go(d): Trusting God in a Storm
description: (Mark 4:35-41): Life can be unrelenting, and when the circumstances conspire to overwhelm us with sorrow, grief or frustration, it can seem as though God has fallen asleep on us. But it is in that helplessness that God wants us to trust that He will always see us through the gale.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2

title: February 5, 2020: Who's the Boss? - Part 1a
description: The world’s burning question is “Who is the boss?”. We associate this term with someone being in charge of others, but this differs from its biblical definition. God’s definition of being the head is based in the “kephale” context of nurturing, growth, and development. When we are in a relationship with the Word and allow Christ to have preeminence in our lives, this relationship causes us to grow, mature, and fulfill our potential.

title: Kingdom Stewardship Volume 1: The Meaning of Stewardship
description: (Genesis 1:26-28): When you leave your home for a weekend and ask someone to house-sit while you're away, you would expect them to take proper care of what's rightfully yours until your return. Just like the house-sitter's given responsibility, God has given each of us the job of stewardship: managing and taking care of His creation. Transform your outlook as you learn how God is the rightful owner of everything, and you only manage what He first puts into your hands.

title: Kingdom Stewardship Volume 1: The Responsibility of Kingdom Stewardship
description: (Matthew 25:14-30): To every person in His kingdom, God has given the ability to be a productive manager under His ownership. But what does God think about those who squander their skills or don’t even put them to use? In this lesson, Tony Evans looks at the parable of the three slaves who were given much in order to expand their master’s kingdom.

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2 :: Kingdom Stewardship Volume 1: The Purpose of Kingdom Stewardship
title: Kingdom Stewardship Volume 1: The Purpose of Kingdom Stewardship
description: (Deuteronomy 8:11-18): As residents of the United States of America, we live and are protected under the covenant known as the Constitution. Similarly, God’s kingdom has a covenant with which all believers are to live under. If you find that you’re not experiencing His kingdom in your life, Tony Evans says it might just be because you are refusing to keep His covenant. Learn all about God’s covenant and why it’s important for His stewards to hold to it.

description: (Matthew 6:25-34) Dr. Tony Evans is the founder and senior pastor of the 10,000-member Oak Cliff Bible Fellowship in Dallas, founder and president of The Urban Alternative, former chaplain of the Dallas Cowboys, and present chaplain of the Dallas Mavericks. His radio and television broadcast, The Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans, can be heard on more than 1,300 radio and television outlets daily in more than 130 countries. The Urban Alternative is the national ministry of Dr. Tony Evans and is dedicated to restoring hope and transforming lives through the proclamation and application of the Word of God.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2 :: Encountering Jesus' Names: Jesus the King
title: Encountering Jesus' Names: Jesus the King
description: (John 18:33-40): While having faith in Christ alone ensures you'll get to spend eternity with Him in heaven, there are far too many people who think they don't have to live under His rule until they get there. Tony Evans says that the reality is He has a kingdom over which He rules: the world and all that dwells in it. In this lesson, learn how Jesus not only wants to be your Savior but also your Ruler.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 3 :: April 22, 2020: The Purpose of the Spirit of Grace - Part 1b
title: April 22, 2020: The Purpose of the Spirit of Grace - Part 1b
description: We must constantly listen for God’s instructions and guidance; hearing from Him is the result of spending time with Him and developing a relationship with Him. Following the Spirit’s lead is critical to any positive change; we must let Him get ahead of us to point out the way to go in life. Not even Jesus did anything without the Holy Spirit.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 3

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 3 :: April 23, 2020: How to Be Lead by the Spirit - Part 1a
title: April 23, 2020: How to Be Lead by the Spirit - Part 1a
description: As Christians, the power of the Spirit is what takes us from average to excellent. When we get born again, we receive the Holy Spirit inside us; this is different than being baptized in the Holy Spirit and letting Him completely influence us. When we allow Him to go ahead of us and we follow, He empowers us to succeed.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 3

title: April 26, 2020: The Contrast - Identity vs. Performance - Part 1b
description: We will not see results in our lives if we ask God to do something He already did, or to do something He told us to do. __str__: Jerry Savelle Ministries :: 2 :: April 19, 2020: The Spirit of Seeing & Knowing - Part 1
title: April 19, 2020: The Spirit of Seeing & Knowing - Part 1
description: Are you ready for what God is about to do? Would you like to discover the biblical keys for knowing God’s plan for you and your family? In this new series, Dr. Jerry Savelle explains the Spirit of Seeing and Knowing. The principles revealed in this series will equip and position you to be ready for what is coming. God doesn’t want you in the dark. He desires to show you what He’s about to do. Without revelation knowledge, God’s people perish and miss out on His blessing. Now is the time to get in-tune with God and live with confidence and faith for His plan. Your best days are ahead! Discover today how God reveals His plan so you can respond in faith and walk in His goodness and purpose.
season: Jerry Savelle Ministries :: 2

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 3 :: May 1, 2020: How to Win Over Depression - Part 1a
title: May 1, 2020: How to Win Over Depression - Part 1a
description: Our emotions can either move us closer to, or away from, God’s will for us. They actually control the direction of our lives. Knowing what the Word says about our feelings allows us to master life instead of letting life master us.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 3

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 3 :: May 4, 2020: How to Win Over Depression - Part 1b
title: May 4, 2020: How to Win Over Depression - Part 1b
description: Our emotions can either move us closer to, or away from, God’s will for us. They actually control the direction of our lives. Knowing what the Word says about our feelings allows us to master life instead of letting life master us.

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 3 :: May 5, 2020: How to Win Over Depression - Part 2a
title: May 5, 2020: How to Win Over Depression - Part 2a
description: Emotions can either be godly or ungodly; one of the most dangerous emotions is depression. The enemy operates in the emotional realm, and his intent is to use our emotions to move us away from the will of God and destroy our lives. When we go to the Word every time we encounter an issue or a problem, we reshape our minds to line up with the spiritual things of God.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 3

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 3 :: May 6, 2020: How to Win Over Depression - Part 2b
title: May 6, 2020: How to Win Over Depression - Part 2b

season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 3

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 3 :: May 7, 2020: How to Win Over Depression - Part 3a
title: May 7, 2020: How to Win Over Depression - Part 3a
description: Feelings are a part of everyone’s lives, but as believers, we do not have to be dominated by them. It is God’s will that we control our emotions and achieve emotional stability. We have been given authority in every realm and we have the power to defeat negative emotions, including depression; therefore, we are accountable for the way we feel. This is something we need to know, so that when our feelings threaten to sweep us away, we can resist the urge. Our emotions can either move us closer to, or away from,God’s will for us. They actually control the direction of our lives. Knowing what the Word says about our feelings allows us to master life instead of letting life master us.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 3

__str__: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 3 :: May 8, 2020: How to Win Over Depression - Part 3b
title: May 8, 2020: How to Win Over Depression - Part 3b
description: Self-control is a gift from God, who gave us the authority to master our feelings. Positive emotions move us toward God’s will for our lives. Conversely, negative emotions, such as depression, move us away from it. We will never be exempt from our feelings, but we can dominate every emotion we experience when we use the Word of God to handle them.
season: Changing Your World with Creflo Dollar :: 3

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2 :: Elijah: Seeing God's Provision
title: Elijah: Seeing God's Provision
description: (1 Kings 17:1-16) - What do you do when you do not have enough? The prophet Elijah faced this same problem when he was led by God to the brook of Cherith where he drank from the brook naturally and was fed by ravens supernaturally. Then the brook dried up and he saw God provide again for him by a poor widow in the town of Zarephath. In this sermon, Tony Evans shares the secrets to understanding the provision of God. The first important thing to remember is that God is your source—everything else is a resource that provides for you. Also, God will often use unexpected sources (unclean ravens) to provide for you as well. When a resource is no longer providing for you, God is merely shifting providers. The way you access His provision is through obedience to His Word and becoming a source of provision in someone else’s life as well.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2 :: Elijah: Committing to the True God
title: Elijah: Committing to the True God
description: (1 Kings 18:20-40) - Tony Evans says there may be undecided voters who have not made up their minds about who to vote for but there should never be undecided Christians. In this sermon, Elijah is on Mt. Carmel, challenging the prophets of Baal and urging the people of God to stop vacillating and commit their hearts to the true and living God. This is so important because, according to Tony, the amount of the supernatural you get to see is linked to your commitment to God as a Christian. If you are undecided about the true God or just not committed to Him during your present crisis, Tony will help you walk through steps to increase your commitment to God. It begins with understanding that the major roadblock to commitment is double mindedness—the habit of giving God divided loyalty instead of giving Him a wholehearted commitment. Once you have dealt with this impediment you will be encouraged to not worry about being outnumbered in a secular society, because you and God are actually a majority, not a minority. The key is to fix your confidence in God and take your stand out of a relationship, not just mere religion. You will know you are committed as you put your spiritual priorities back in order and as you allow God’s Word to have the final say in the decisions you make in life.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2 :: Elijah: Praying and Waiting for God's Timing
title: Elijah: Praying and Waiting for God's Timing
description: (1 Kings 18:41-46) - Elijah tells Ahab that it is going to rain. His fervent and effectual prayer opens up the heavens and rain comes to an area that desperately needs it. Have you ever wanted to see your prayer life become more powerful? In this sermon, Tony Evans moves us from ritualistic communication to relational communication as we start to pray more effectively and see God work in our lives. Tony tells us that prayer is the point of contact between God’s power and His provision in our lives. Prayer is God’s mechanism for grabbing the invisible and making it visible in our lives. But in our prayers we are not “making God do something.” Rather, prayer allows God to release His decreed will in our lives. By studying and understanding God’s Word, we are encouraged to continue praying until something happens!
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2

__str__: Jerry Savelle Ministries :: 2 :: May 24, 2020: A Set Time - Part 1
title: May 24, 2020: A Set Time - Part 1
description: God is faithful to keep His promises. When God makes a promise He sees that it is fulfilled no matter what is going on in our personal lives or in the country. Nothing can derail God's promises for our lives. In this powerful 2 part series, Dr. Savelle shows us from the Word of God three key points: How to triumph over opposition; How God’s presence brings miracles; and How to embrace your full potential in Christ.
season: Jerry Savelle Ministries :: 2

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2 :: Elijah: Encouragement that Calms Fears
title: Elijah: Encouragement that Calms Fears
description: (1 Kings 19:1-6) - In this sermon, we learn that spiritual people can sometimes struggle and get discouraged. The prophet Elijah had God’s hand on him and still became discouraged, even suicidal. This is not an issue only with Elijah. Many of God’s greatest servants battled discouragement including Moses, Job, and the apostle Paul. This sermon helps us learn how to deal with discouragement and the need many of us have for a miracle in our minds. Tony Evans walks us through the cause of discouragement, which is the loss of something or an unexpected change in our expectations. Also, the catalyst for discouragement is our thoughts because they affect our emotions and what we feel. The enemy’s job is to keep us living under a threat and to control us by winning the battle for our minds. Tony gives us hope by reminding us that discouragement does not have to own us. We can take back control by addressing the physical aspects of our lives that may be leading to our discouragement. This should be accompanied by an honest conversation about where we are emotionally with the Lord. In this evaluation of our emotions we should not develop a victim’s mentality because, while circumstances may not change, they don’t have to control us. According to Tony, what will get us refocused is running toward God’s presence and seeking out godly friends who understand His power and can walk with us during the dark times of life.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2 :: Elijah: Living a Life that Lasts
title: Elijah: Living a Life that Lasts
description: (2 Kings 2:1-14) - In this sermon, Tony Evans challenges us to ask the question, “How much of God am I leaving behind?” A true legacy transcends material things and makes a big deal about God. It is within this context that we find Elijah transferring the power of God to Elisha. (Psalm 71:18) Tony will show you the necessary components needed to pass the baton of faith to those who follow you and how to leave something that will truly last forever. Tony gives us a strategic way to pass faith on to those who follow us. It starts with a desire similar to Elisha’s, who wanted twice as much God as Elijah possessed so that he could do more for God. Secondly, we must be devoted, just like Elisha, to seeing things from a spiritual perspective. If you want to get more of God, you need to be detached from other things that are holding you back from the supernatural. What are you willing to have less of so that you can have more of God? Elisha had to leave a business behind to follow in the footsteps of Elijah. But one of the key aspects of leaving a legacy is the ability to disciple and empower someone else so they can correctly inherit the spiritual mantle of leadership. As Elijah did for Elisha, if we are to pass on a spiritual legacy we must depend on God to guide us as we take another person from development to their God given destiny.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2

__str__: Jerry Savelle Ministries :: 2 :: June 7, 2020: Quitting is Not an Option - Part 1
title: June 7, 2020: Quitting is Not an Option - Part 1
description: 1 John 5:4 says, "…whatsoever is born of God overcometh the world: and this is the victory that overcometh the world, even our faith." The Word says we are overcomers, and God will never say it's over until you win, but how do you continue to stand while the battle is still going? In this teaching, Dr. Jerry Savelle takes us through to the Word to show us how to conquer the temptation to quit, how to stay in faith for our victory, how to stay focused on God by developing patience, and why we should make the decision to never quit.
season: Jerry Savelle Ministries :: 2

title: The Jesus Challenge: A Challenge to Overcome
description: (1 John 5:1-5) - The Bible teaches that through Jesus, we have overcome sin. But in reality, all of us still struggle with sin, even though we love the Lord and desire to serve Him. Tony Evans explains the reason for this disconnect and offers the key to experiencing true victory over sin.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2 :: Kingdom Stewardship Volume 1: The Meaning of Stewardship
title: Kingdom Stewardship Volume 1: The Meaning of Stewardship
description: (Genesis 1:26-28): When you leave your home for a weekend and ask someone to house-sit while you’re away, you would expect them to take proper care of what’s rightfully yours until your return. Just like the house-sitter’s given responsibility, God has given each of us the job of stewardship: managing and taking care of His creation. Transform your outlook as you learn how God is the rightful owner of everything, and you only manage what He first puts into your hands.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2

__str__: Jerry Savelle Ministries :: 2 :: June 21, 2020: Quitting is Not an Option - Part 3
title: June 21, 2020: Quitting is Not an Option - Part 3
description: 1 John 5:4 says, "…whatsoever is born of God overcometh the world: and this is the victory that overcometh the world, even our faith." The Word says we are overcomers, and God will never say it's over until you win, but how do you continue to stand while the battle is still going? In this teaching, Dr. Jerry Savelle takes us through to the Word to show us how to conquer the temptation to quit, how to stay in faith for our victory, how to stay focused on God by developing patience, and why we should make the decision to never quit.
season: Jerry Savelle Ministries :: 2

description: (Revelation 3:1-6, Sardis) - What’s on the outside isn’t always what’s on the inside. title: August 16, 2020: God is Not Going to Allow You to Fail - Part 1
description: God has many promises in His Word assuring that He has designed a life of victory for the Believer, including the scripture in 2 Corinthians 12:9 which says, "My grace is sufficient for thee: for my strength is made perfect in weakness..." However, most Christians today who love God are living below their level of victory that God wants for their lives. If God's grace is sufficient, why don't more of us walk in the fact that we're immune to failure? Dr. Jerry Savelle has a powerful series for you on how to raise your expectation in God to see victory in every area of your life, how to stand on the Word until your circumstances change, and how vital it is to develop a no-quit attitude if you're going to live a life free from failure.

title: Believing is Seeing: Trusting God in a Storm
description: (Mark 4:35-41): Life can be unrelenting, and when the circumstances conspire to overwhelm us with sorrow, grief or frustration, it can seem as though God has fallen asleep on us. But it is in that helplessness that God wants us to trust that He will always see us through the gale.

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2 :: American Idols: Idol – Eyes
title: American Idols: Idol – Eyes
description: (Ezekiel 14:1-8): Our God is a great God—but it’s not always an easy task to remember that He’s in control. In fact, the less capable you think He is, the more likely you are to look to other means such as idols to fulfill a need that you don’t think God will. That’s why in "Idol Eyes", Tony Evans takes a step back to show you a broader perspective on the dangers and concerns of idolatry in today’s society.

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2 :: Encountering God's Process
title: Encountering God's Process
description: Coming up on this week’s broadcast of The Alternative with Tony Evans: For you to have a divine encounter with God, there is a process that must first take place. Tony Evans says that until we become stripped of our self-sufficiency, God often remains a distant concept instead of a dynamic reality. In Encountering God's Process, you’ll look at the importance of giving up your independence to enable you to experience a new level of His reality. To experience more valuable lessons on the truths of God’s Word, be sure to visit us at tonyevans.org."
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2 :: God and Citizenship
title: God and Citizenship
description: Coming up on this week’s broadcast of The Alternative with Tony Evans: The will of God can be a mysterious thing for both old and new believers alike, but Tony Evans says that it doesn’t have to be. If you seek to understand the connection between surrendering to God and experiencing the visible manifestation of His kingdom in your life, this lesson titled The Priority of Prayer will show you how the simple act of prayer can harmonize your will to become the same as your heavenly Father’s. To experience more valuable lessons on the truths of God’s Word, be sure to visit us at tonyevans.org."
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2 :: The Protection of Prayer
title: The Protection of Prayer
description: Coming up on this week’s broadcast of The Alternative with Tony Evans: In the final words of the Lord’s prayer, Jesus ends His model with a request for protection—but from what? While Satan’s goal is to damage our fellowship with God by any means, Jesus combats that by sharing the importance of protection through prayer. In The Protection of Prayer, you’ll learn all about the enemy’s use of temptation along with the protection we have from it through Christ. To experience more valuable lessons on the truths of God’s Word, be sure to visit us at tonyevans.org."
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2 :: Lords Prayer: The Purpose of Prayer
title: Lords Prayer: The Purpose of Prayer
description: For many people, the concept of prayer is often seen as nothing more than a tedious yet necessary exercise of Christian life. But prayer is so much more than something to be marked off your daily checklist, and in The Lord’s Prayer, Dr. Tony Evans will examine the teachings of Jesus to show you how you can transform your prayer into an exciting opportunity of communication with God.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 2

__str__: Believer's Voice of Victory :: 5 :: Understanding Biblical Timing
title: Understanding Biblical Timing
description: Why does God delay judgment? Join Kenneth Copeland and Professor Greg Stephens on Believer’s Voice of Victory as they discuss the patterns in events throughout different times in the Bible. Learn the importance of understanding biblical timing and how you can be instrumental in fulfilling the will and plan of God.
season: Believer's Voice of Victory :: 5

__str__: Believer's Voice of Victory :: 5 :: The Difference Between Sin, Iniquity and Transgression
title: The Difference Between Sin, Iniquity and Transgression
description: What does "when sin is full" mean? Watch Kenneth Copeland and Professor Greg Stephens on Believer’s Voice of Victory as they continue to unpack how the Bible defines iniquity and God’s certain response. Learn the difference between sin, iniquity and transgression and how you can protect your spirit from all three.
season: Believer's Voice of Victory :: 5

__str__: Believer's Voice of Victory :: 5 :: Why Judgment Comes
title: Why Judgment Comes
description: When does the judgment of God come? Join Kenneth Copeland and Professor Greg Stephens on Believer’s Voice of Victory as they explain why judgment comes when the cup of iniquity is full. Learn from the story of Noah why God delays, what causes God to finally respond to the sins of the world, and how it relates to us today.
season: Believer's Voice of Victory :: 5

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3 :: Why Men Matter
title: Why Men Matter
description: The very idea of “masculinity” these days is thought of as (at best) outdated and (at worst) downright evil. But in this lesson, Dr. Tony Evans begins a new series of messages that redefine the term from a biblical perspective and explain why it’s a vital ingredient in God’s recipe for humanity.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3 :: The Call to Biblical Manhood
title: The Call to Biblical Manhood
description: Who decides what it means to be a real man? Too often, we leave that job to the people who write action movies or TV shows. But in this lesson, Dr. Tony Evans explores what the biblical model of manhood really looks like.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3 :: Men Covered by God
title: Men Covered by God
description: Connecting men with the leadership power God has given them requires a clear understanding of who we are… and who we aren’t. Join Dr. Tony Evans as he explains why exercising God’s authority begins by learning to submit to it.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3 :: The Dominion of a Man
title: The Dominion of a Man
description: “Dominion” is a word you don’t hear a lot in everyday conversation, but it’s the name of an often-misunderstood biblical concept Dr. Tony Evans is here to tell us about. Join him for this look at the mission God gave to men and the resources He provides to carry it out.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3 :: Revival in the Valley of Dry Bones
title: Revival in the Valley of Dry Bones
description: While global warming advocates talk about the world getting hotter, the spiritual climate (especially in our country) seems to be cooling off fast. Join Dr. Tony Evans in this lesson as he talks about how that trend can be reversed.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3 :: Men Who Beat the Odds
title: Men Who Beat the Odds
description: A lot of times, when we try to size up our circumstances, the odds against us can seem overwhelming. But Dr. Tony Evans is here to tell us about some important factors we may have left out of the equation.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3 :: A Tale of Two Men
title: A Tale of Two Men
description: We learn by watching examples—some we’ll want to follow and others we’ll want to avoid. Join Dr. Tony Evans as he introduces us to one of each and tells us a “tale of two men” which takes a look at what it takes to build a life that matters.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3 :: The Legacy of a Man
title: The Legacy of a Man
description: When our lives are over, it’s up to our children to carry on our name. But in this lesson, Dr. Tony Evans says that they should be carrying on something else as well. Join him for this look at the most important legacy a man can leave to his family.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3 :: Lame Man Walking
title: Lame Man Walking
description: Join Dr. Tony Evans as he tells the story of a lame beggar who got more help from Jesus than he expected. In this lesson, you’ll take a look at why living like a spiritual cripple can be habit-forming and how men can find the strength to stand up and start walking by faith.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3 :: Begging for a Blessing
title: Begging for a Blessing
description: Blessings come from God, but not just from God. Join Dr. Tony Evans as he touches on the importance of the blessings that we pass on… and what to do if they were never passed on to us. It’s a look at the crucial importance of handing down a spiritual heritage to our children.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3 :: Why Men Need Each Other
title: Why Men Need Each Other
description: If you were interested in flying a plane or performing surgery, you’d go to flight school or medical school. But where do men go to learn to be godly men? That’s Dr. Evans’ subject for this lesson as he talks about why men need the church.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3 :: Stones of Remembrance
title: Stones of Remembrance
description: Many churches suffer from a lack of male leadership… even male attendance. But in this lesson, Dr. Evans explains why men need the church even more than the church needs them in this lesson on what it means to be a “kingdom man".
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3

description: In this message, He speaks on the qualities of the Roman centurion and the faith he had for Jesus to be able to heal his servant.
season: Brian Houston TV :: 4

__str__: Brian Houston TV :: 4 :: A Magnetic Gathering
title: A Magnetic Gathering
description: Pastor Brian Houston preaches from Isaiah chapter 60. He encourages us to reflect on God’s goodness and to believe for the promises still yet to be fulfilled in our lives by keeping God at the center of everything we do.
season: Brian Houston TV :: 4

__str__: Brian Houston TV :: 4 :: 'Even if He Doesn't' Faith
title: 'Even if He Doesn't' Faith
description: In this episode, Pastor Brian encourages us to journey through the disappointments we have from unanswered prayer with trust that God will do the impossible. What would it look like in our lives to have 'even if He doesn't' kind of faith?
season: Brian Houston TV :: 4

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3 :: Divine Disruption
title: Divine Disruption
description: We’ve all learned recently how easily our idea of “normal life” can be turned upside down. But in this lesson, Dr. Tony Evans will explain how God is using the pandemic for his purposes and will helps us make sure we do not miss the point of this divine disruption.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3 :: Concept of Faith
title: Concept of Faith
description: Too many people, faith is a feeling—a sense of confidence or optimism. But in this lesson, Dr. Tony Evans explains that real faith is something we live out, no matter what our emotions are telling us.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3 :: Abel: The Worship of Faith
title: Abel: The Worship of Faith
description: Have you ever wondered what it really means to live your life walking by faith? Faith can be easily described as acting like God is telling the truth before you see the results, but that’s much easier said than done. Join Dr. Tony Evans as he takes a look at the Hall of Faith: a collection of Old Testament heroes and their experiences used to teach New Testament Christians what it means to live your life through faith.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 3

title: The Purpose of Detours
description: Wouldn’t it be great if God could lead you right to the earthly calling He had in store for you? Unfortunately for us, God rarely takes his children to their destiny in the way they might expect. Tony Evans says that in order to fully experience God’s destiny for you, you need to understand the detours He might provide along the way. In this lesson, discover how God uses Joseph’s biggest detour yet in order to begin developing the plans He has in store for him.

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 4 :: The Protection of Prayer
title: The Protection of Prayer
description: In the final words of the Lord’s prayer, Jesus ends His lesson of prayer given to His disciples with a request for protection—but from what? While Satan’s goal is to damage our fellowship with God by any means, Jesus combats that by sharing the importance of protection through prayer. In this lesson, you’ll learn everything you need to know about the enemy’s use of temptation as well as the protection we have from it through Christ.
season: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 4

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 4 :: The Purpose of Prayer
title: The Purpose of Prayer
description: Jesus closes the Lord’s Prayer with the famous doxology, “For Thine is the kingdom, the power and the glory, forever. Amen.” In light of the rest of the Lord’s Prayer, we are led to praise. In this message, Tony Evans explains that we are looking forward to His kingdom. We recognize His power. And we give Him His deserved glory. And the praise will go on forevermore.

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 4 :: The Divine Imperative
title: The Divine Imperative
description: Maintaining a balance in your Christian walk can be very difficult. On one hand, being too heavenly-minded will make you no earthly good, while on the other hand, being too earthly-minded means you are no heavenly good. But true balance occurs when you can bring good to earth through your heavenly mindset. Learn more about maintaining the Biblically-based balance that Tony Evans likes to refer to as “The Divine Imperative.”.

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 4 :: Prayer and Spiritual Warfare
title: Prayer and Spiritual Warfare
description: If you keep a spare tire in the back of your car, you’ll know that it’s only kept there for when something goes flat. Tony Evans says many Christians treat prayer like a spare tire—if nothing’s going flat in life, there’s no need for it. But the Bible says to pray at all times, and in this message, you’ll find that by doing so you’re preparing yourself for the inevitable occurrence of any spiritual warfare that may strike.

__str__: The Urban Alternative with Dr. Tony Evans :: 4 :: The Protection of Prayer
title: The Protection of Prayer
description: In the final words of the Lord’s prayer, Jesus ends His lesson of prayer given to His disciples with a request for protection—but from what? While Satan’s goal is to damage our fellowship with God by any means, Jesus combats that by sharing the importance of protection through prayer. In this lesson, you’ll learn everything you need to know about the enemy’s use of temptation as well as the protection we have from it through Christ.

__str__: Miracles Happen! :: 1 :: Celebration To Betrayal
title: Celebration To Betrayal
description: Passion week is coming, as we get ready to kick it off with this coming Palm Sunday! Join me as we dive deeper into looking at some of the most unexpected turn of events that happened in the Bible during this time in history. Passion week is a time to reflect on all of what Jesus paid for your salvation and how Jesus fulfilled his purpose in God’s plan for redemption for humanity. Get ready to uncover many profound lessons within each of the stories of Jesus that we will read about together. Be sure to grab your pen and journal, as you won’t want to miss out on discovering the 3 most common threads that run throughout the intentional steps that Jesus took as His time on Earth was coming to a close. Jesus is with you and He loves you! Jesus has already given you everything you need to get through the plot twists and curve balls thrown your way in life to come out victorious. Surrender to Him and trust Him with your outcomes as new life, new hope, and greater faith await you. Happy Early Holy Week!
season: Miracles Happen! :: 1

__str__: Miracles Happen! :: 1 :: The Gardens Of Your Life
title: The Gardens Of Your Life
description: Easter is just around the corner! Are you ready to reconcile the pain of the past with God’s promises for a better future? Do ever feel like you need a fresh start or a new beginning? Well, get ready as we are moving into a new season as spring approaches. Spring brings us a season where we get to celebrate and honor some of the most significant days in the life of Jesus. A time to remember the victory and new life Jesus brought us through the resurrection. Join me for Miracles Happens as we dig deeper into the word of God in this resurrection season of Easter. Learn to flourish and grow in the things of God and what He has called us to do. It’s time to believe in the resurrection power of Christ again! From old to new, death to life, from sickness to health, and defeat to victory, God can turn it all around!

__str__: Miracles Happen! :: 1 :: Double Portions
title: Double Portions
description: In today's episode of Miracles Happen, we are bringing you a word about the secrets of increase from Cindy Jacobs. Cindy Jacobs is a dear friend and trusted prophet, who sits on the Apostolic Council of Prophetic Elders, who have been meeting for over 22 years now. Cindy is ready to share revelations about blessings through wisdom she gained from the prayer of Jabez in 1 Chronicles. God wants to bless you, and He loves you. He only wants good for you. Are you ready to receive those blessings? We have not because we ask not. Tune in today and learn how to take action like Jabez, and be blessed by God. God has dreams for you, and one of those is for you to be blessed!
season: Miracles Happen! :: 1

__str__: Miracles Happen! :: 1 :: Power of the Prophetic
title: Power of the Prophetic
description: Tune in for an amazing episode with our guest, pastor, author, and speaker, Sherman Dumas. He is ready to share with you about the importance of the prophetic word of God, and how we can activate it inside of us to share with others. Just as Pastor Sherman shares his story on how his life was saved by the power of a prophetic word, a word from God can shift everything around for you, too. It is through the word of God shared that we can gain a new level of vision and clarity to what God is bringing us into. Are you ready to receive and share when God speaks to you? Join us as Pastor Sherman helps you get free, mobilized, and set to walk in all that God has called you to do.
season: Miracles Happen! :: 1

__str__: Miracles Happen! :: 1 :: A Prophetic Move Of God!
title: A Prophetic Move Of God!
description: Are you ready for another great Miracles Happens episode? Tune in as special guest Bishop Bill Hamon joins us this week! He brings a word on the prophetic and discusses the accompany of prophets that God is raising up and the importance and relevance of it today. We are moving into a time like we have never seen before, and Bishop Bill Hamon is set to impart wisdom of growth to you. God is moving, and we need to be ready as His hands and feet to also move when He calls. It’s time to step into what God is calling you to do!
season: Miracles Happen! :: 1

description:

__str__: Miracles Happen! :: 1 :: Covering Our Veterans
title: Covering Our Veterans
description: Today on Miracles Happen! we are honoring our veterans and praying for total and complete freedom. We are so thankful to our veterans for serving our country and for the sacrifices they made to protect our freedom. If you are a veteran or have any form of PTSD, trauma or anxiety then today is the day for a miracle of healing.
season: Miracles Happen! :: 1

__str__: Miracles Happen! :: 1 :: Miracle Missions
title: Miracle Missions
description: Meet Joe Kirkwood on Miracles Happen this week as we share about the vision of what God has called us to do! Missions are an incredible part of Joan Hunter Ministries.
season: Miracles Happen! :: 1

__str__: Miracles Happen! :: 1 :: Provision On The Nile
title: Provision On The Nile
description: In this season of thanksgiving we want to give God thanks in remembrance of what He did, not only at the cross but continuously in our lives. In our recent mission trip to Africa, I was able to visit the incredible Nile River. The Nile is considered to be a critical lifeline for the entire continent of Africa. It is a major trade route for goods. It is the longest river in the world, 4100 miles long. It is known for annual flooding, necessary for several reasons. It provides nutrient rich soaking for the soil and helps create productive farmland.
season: Miracles Happen! :: 1

__str__: Miracles Happen! :: 1 :: The Lion in the Darkness
title: The Lion in the Darkness
description: Are you in a fight for your destiny? Have you ever felt blocked in the pursuit of your destiny? Are you facing obstacles and barriers you just can't understand? I was reminded what it can be like when there is an assignment of death over your destiny.
season: Miracles Happen! :: 1

__str__: Miracles Happen! :: 1 :: Attack on Entebbe
title: Attack on Entebbe
description: Pastor and Mission leader Joe Kirkwood shares of his arrival and beginning of missions in war-torn Entebbe, Uganda.
season: Miracles Happen! :: 1

__str__: Miracles Happen! :: 1 :: Angels- God’s Messengers
title: Angels- God’s Messengers
description: Merry Christmas! Today on Miracles Happen we are talking about how God uses angels to fulfill His will on earth. Some lack awareness of the activity of angels around their life and many people are highly aware of their presence. God uses angels in many ways, such as messengers, ministers, helpers and servants. They can care, protect and guide us in life.
season: Miracles Happen! :: 1

__str__: Miracles Happen! :: 1 :: Psalm 23 for 2023
title: Psalm 23 for 2023
description: Happy New Year! It's going to be a great year, where God pulls you into greater intimacy and show how much He really cares for you. No matter what season you are currently walking through, just know that God is with you. We are in a season of transition and shifting. God is leading you into a more beautiful place. As I was praying for the newest episode of Miracles Happen, what kept coming back to me was Psalm 23 for 2023. The Lord is my shepherd. Many have been walking through a very difficult and challenging season, and I want to encourage you that His presence will give you comfort to walk through the hard times. As our faithful shepherd, God is leading and guiding us through the deep valleys. God wants you to know that He sees it all. God is taking us from where we are to a place of abundance, prosperity, a place of plenty. A place where He heals our every wound and provides our every need. As we embark on the new year 2023, know that God has great plans for you and your best days are ahead!
season: Miracles Happen! :: 1

__str__: Miracles Happen! :: 1 :: Walking Out Your Destiny
title: Walking Out Your Destiny
description: What is limiting or stopping you from doing what God has called you to do? We’ve all been called to do something we know we can’t do because this allows room for God to step in and work. God’s dreams for us are much bigger than our own dreams because we often limit them to only what we know we can do. It’s time for you to get out of your comfort zone and step into God’s zone. Tune in this week to start confessing the Word of God over your life as you take steps to walk out your destiny.

We are so thankful and appreciative of all that those in service, the veterans, and their families do for our country and freedom every single day. Join us this week for Miracles Happen as we honor our veterans and their families. You don't want to miss out as I share some amazing testimonies of healing, restoration, and turnaround from PTSD, TBI, depressions, trauma, grief, injuries and more. Just as those in the testimonies shared about today, God is ready to walk with you on your road to healing. God wants you free and completely healed in every way and area of your life. It’s time to break the chains weighing you down, and start walking in freedom and healing!

__str__: Miracles Happen! :: 1 :: Setting The Table - A Thanksgiving Message
title: Setting The Table - A Thanksgiving Message
description:
I am so excited for this special time of the year & I can’t wait to share it with you! It’s THANKSGIVING TIME! A wonderful time to gather with family & friends to make memories and come together to thank God for all He has done for us. Not only in this season should we be thankful for all that we have, but all year long we should embrace an attitude of gratitude. 

Join me this week for Miracles Happen as we take the kitchen and I share my family’s all-time favorite Thanksgiving meal. Not only that, but I will also share with you about having a grateful heart, how you can prepare your Thanksgiving table to welcome your guests, the healing & freeing power of forgiveness, and sowing seeds of kindness & peace that can open doors. Get ready with me to celebrate this amazing time to give thanks, not only for family and friends, but also to our loving Heavenly Father, who sacrifices so much for us and continually provides provision and blessings for us. You don’t want to miss out!
season: Miracles Happen! :: 1

__str__: Miracles Happen! :: 1 :: The Symbols Of Christmas
title: The Symbols Of Christmas
description:
Join me in this enlightening episode of Miracles Happen as we uncover the hidden symbolism behind your favorite Christmas decorations!

From Christmas trees to candy canes, we will reveal the mysteries how each ornament points to the message of Jesus and the true essence of the holiday season. Discover the deeper meaning behind your festive decor and learn how to keep the focus on celebrating God's greatest gift during this special time of year. 

Don't miss this insightful exploration of Christmas symbolism!

__str__: Miracles Happen! :: 2 :: New Beginnings
title: New Beginnings
description:
Join me for a profound episode of Miracles Happen as I share powerful insight to help you navigate 2024 with faith and expectation!

In this episode, we will dive deep into the theme of finding hope and healing in a world that sometimes seems chaotic. Discover how to silence the voices of fear and anxiety and instead listen to the still small voice of God. With personal stories and powerful prayers, I hope to inspire you to face the future with confidence. 

Whether you're looking for divine guidance, seeking healing, or simply in need of spiritual upliftment, this episode is for you! Expect to receive inspiration, encouragement, and a renewed sense of purpose as we embark on the journey of 2024 together.

Don't miss out on this opportunity to experience transformation and miracles in your life. Tune in and be a part of the miracles unfolding in 2024!
season: Miracles Happen! :: 2

__str__: Miracles Happen! :: 2 :: the gift of Tongues
title: the gift of Tongues
description: You don’t want to miss this exciting new episode of Miracles Happen! Join in and take a trip with me to Africa. See what God had called me to do earlier in 2023 that I had no idea He would lead me to where He did. Has God ever spoke something to you or called you to do a certain thing, and it left you shocked and questioning what He was asking of you? In those situations, you have a choice to make: whether you put your trust in God to walk by faith in following where He is calling, or if you avoid it and do something other than what He is asking of you. I want to share with you how, for me, I was able to have courage in saying yes to God’s call. Through my obedience, I was able to see miraculous miracles and the move of God in Ghana. Just as the anointing of the Holy Spirit changed the lives of those in Ghana, you too have the power to see the manifestation of miracles through Christ Jesus. It’s time to step up and into the calling God has for you!
season: Miracles Happen! :: 2
